title: orange pineapple dessert
directions: Cut all fruit and slightly drain.
Keep about 1 to 2 cups of juice.
Blend everything together (fruit, coconut, sour cream and marshmallows).
Put in refrigerator for about 3 or 4 hours.
Before you are ready to serve, add remaining juice to desired consistency.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Bake about 1 hour or more in 300° oven.
Don't need frosting.

title: brigid's chicken liver pate
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in blender.
Blend well.
Add chicken livers.
Blend 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend 2 minutes more.
Pour into greased pan.
Cover with greased foil. Place in pan of water.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Remove foil. Cool 4 hours.
Serve.

title: hot spiced pecans
directions: Spray pan with nonstick spray.
Melt butter in baking pan. Stir in salt and add pecans.
Mix well until nuts are thoroughly coated.
Add Worcestershire, pepper, cinnamon, and Tabasco and toss again.
Place in 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir frequently until nuts are brown and crisp.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: magic lemon meringue pie
directions: Blend together milk, lemon juice, grated lemon rind or extract and egg yolks.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with meringue and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook rice according to package except use chicken broth instead of water.
Mix all together and bake in 2-quart casserole at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with salad and bread.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: mom's butterscotch coconut drops
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt. Cream the butter. Gradually add the brown sugar and white sugar, creaming well. Blend in the eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Add dry ingredients gradually.
Mix thoroughly. Stir in the butterscotch morsels and walnuts.
Mix well. Chill dough 1 hour. Drop by rounded teaspoonful into the finely chopped coconut.
Roll to coat.
Form into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes until golden at edges. Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: german chocolate cake icing
directions: In a large skillet, combine all ingredients, except coconut and pecans. Cook on low heat for 15 to 20 minutes, until mixture thickens, stirring constantly. Add coconut and pecans. Mix completely. Apply to layers of cake and top.

title: nadine's mock beef burgundy
directions: Begin about 3 1/2 hours before serving time.
Brown meat in little shortening in Dutch oven.
Sprinkle with flour, salt, thyme and pepper.
Toss to coat meat.
Add onion.
In a small bowl, stir water and beef bouillon cubes until dissolved.
Pour into pot.
Add vegetable flakes, cranberry juice and bay leaf.
Cover and cook on low heat until meat is tender.
Remove bay leaf.
May serve with cooked rice.
Serves 5.

title: tina tacos
directions: Brown meat and drain.
In greased muffin tin push biscuits in cavities.
Spoon in hamburger seasoned with taco powder and tomato sauce.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: delicious cheese, eggs and spinach brunch dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Turn into greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish or casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let sit 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: To confectioners sugar, add cocoa, salt and vanilla.
Add coffee and mix thoroughly.
Add butter and mix well.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook onions and zucchini in 1/2 cup margarine for 10 minutes. Beat eggs and mix into cheese.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a deep-dish pie pan where rolls are patted to form crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light brown and bubbly.

title: zucchini lasagne
directions: Slice the zucchini lengthwise into 1/4-inch slices.
Mix the flour with the salt and pepper (or alternate no salt seasoning) and dip both sides of zucchini slices into the mixture.

In a large nonstick skillet, heat the oil and fry the zucchini slices, half at a time, over medium heat until they are golden, turning them once. Remove the zucchini to a platter covered with a paper towel.
In a medium bowl, combine the Ricotta, egg white and whole egg, oregano and 3 tablespoons of the Parmesan.
In the bottom of a baking pan, approximately 12 x 8 x 2-inches, spread 1 cup of the spaghetti sauce, top with half the zucchini slices, then half the Ricotta mixture and half the Mozzarella.
Repeat the layers.
Sprinkle lasagne with the remaining Parmesan.
Bake the lasagne in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until lasagne is bubbly.
Let the lasagne stand for about 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix together asparagus juice, soup and crackers.
In a greased dish, layer asparagus, mixture and grated cheese.
End with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: rice n sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain (crumbled up). Mix all ingredients together in a baking dish and cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel biscuit ring around
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease a 12-cup Bundt pan.
In small saucepan, combine brown sugar, chopped nuts, margarine and water.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Place in a large bowl. Pour sugar mixture, that has been heated, over biscuits to coat. Toss lightly.
Spoon into pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Take out of oven and let stand for 3 minutes.
Turn onto plate.
Serve warm.

title: butter cookies (no egg)(small crunchy cookies)
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll out dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch circles.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: crock-pot steak
directions: Cut
steak in serving pieces.
Flour steak and brown in skillet in a small amount of oil.
Put in crock-pot;
sprinkle a little
flour over steak to thicken.
Pour tomatoes, string beans, soy
sauce
and
molasses
over
steak.
Cut pepper in strips and add
to
mixture;
stir
well.
Cook 6 to 8 hours. Serve over rice!

title: lime party salad
directions: Melt in top of a double boiler the marshmallows and milk. Pour hot mixture over the jello. Stir until dissolved.
Beat in the cream cheese. Beat until cheese dissolves. Add the pineapple. Cool. Blend
in the heavy cream, already whipped, mayonnaise and food coloring. Chill until firm.
Will serve 12.
This is really good.
Pretty when served at Christmas or St. Patrick's Day.

title: creole chicken with garlic
directions: Cut peppers into 1-inch pieces.
Chop the onions; slice the garlic.
In Dutch oven, heat oil.
Salt and pepper the meat.
Cook pieces until browned on all sides; remove meat and set aside. Lower heat.
Add garlic, onions, peppers and 1 teaspoon salt to pan; cook for about 10 minutes, until soft.
Raise heat.
Add wine; cook until liquid is gone.
Add tomatoes, oregano, cayenne and the meat.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until meat is tender, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and lard; add sour milk, prunes and flour. Beat well and bake 45 minutes or until done in a 375° oven.

title: summer sandwiches
directions: Cream the cream cheese, salt, lemon juice and mayonnaise until fluffy.
Fold in the remaining ingredients.
Mix and chill several hours.
Use in sandwiches or with crackers.

title: betty dunn's rum cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Crumble chopped nuts in bottom. Place cake and pudding mixes in large mixing bowl.
Add rum, water, oil and eggs.
Mix for two minutes.
Pour batter into cake pan and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from oven. Leave cake in pan and pour on the following hot rum glaze while cake is still hot.
Leave cake in pan to cool for 30 minutes.

title: bacon biscuit balls
directions: In bowl, combine biscuit mix with milk, pepper, bacon, green pepper and onion.
Roll out dough 1/2-inch thick, then with jigger cut and place on pan and bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Brush with beaten egg.
Serve warm or cold with dip.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt brown sugar, cream and butter in saucepan until dissolved; cool.
Beat in powdered sugar.
Sprinkle pecans on top.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Mix dressing, macaroni, tuna, celery, green pepper, onions and pimento.
Season to taste.
Refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce-lined plates.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple in pan.
Mix cake mix, nuts, and coconut together.
Put on top of pie filling and pineapple.
Slice margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wiener on the stick
directions: Mix shortening, egg and milk. Add dry mustard, paprika and red pepper to flour. Mix well. Dip wieners in mixture real good and fry in deep fat until brown.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix.
Put oil in skillet and fry.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until foamy.
Add cream of tartar. Beat until stiff.
Fold in sugar and flavoring.
Sift a small amount of flour over the mixture and fold in carefully.
Continue until all is used.
Pour into an angel food cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 275°.
After first 30 minutes, increase heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mounds cake
directions: Divide into 3 layers. Bake as directed on package.

title: oh no, what do i bring to the potluck
directions: Hop onto Gold Wing and race as fast as you can without speeding, of course, to the store.
Buy 1 or 2 containers of potato salad or cole slaw.
Sneak into the produce aisle and thieve a small sprig of parsley.
(For those with a conscience you can bag and pay for this.)
When you get back to the motorcycle, dump salad into bowl and top with parsley.
Unless you are already sweating, you can spritz face to insinuate effort.

title: punch(slush)
directions: Mix jello in hot water and sugar.
Add juices.
Add water to make 1 gallon.
Freeze in a plastic container (gallon milk jug). When ready to serve, cut top of gallon jug and pour ginger ale over to thaw (1 to 3 hours).
Makes 32 cups to gallon.
Do not use glass punch bowl.

title: spicy tuna salad
directions: Fry potatoes in deep fryer.
While they are cooking, prepare rest of dish.

title: spiced beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a serving dish. Sprinkle top with chopped pecans.
Warm in microwave or serve in a chafing dish.
Serve with crackers.

title: minnie's powdered sugar pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Blend in flour well.
Bake at 325° for about one hour.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in greased casserole dish.
Add mixed vegetables over chicken; do not stir.
Mix soup and broth together; pour over vegetables.

title: lemon custard jello
directions: Cool Jell-O slightly and pour into 6 x 9 glass baking dish. Add pineapple. Slice bananas on top of Jell-O mixture. Cover with marshmallows and gently pat them down to moisten them. Refrigerate until firm.

title: overnight slaw
directions: Mix first three ingredients, and cook until syrupy.
Let stand until cool.
Mix vegetables with dressing and let stand overnight.
Keeps well in refrigerator for 2 weeks, and also freezes well.

title: diabetic sugarless cookies
directions: Add 1 cup water to raisins, apples and dates.
Boil until all water is absorbed.
Cool.
Then add oil, sweetener, soda, eggs, vanilla, flour and nuts.
Mix well and refrigerate until chilled. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
You can use coconut or part pecans and coconut mixed.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
May store in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine in order given.
Pour into greased pans, 2/3 full. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean in 350° oven.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain, mix all ingredients into a large crock pot.
Do not drain the corn tomatoes or beans.

title: red onion pizza
directions: Saute the vegetables in oil about 5 minutes. Add salt, sugar and tomatoes. Simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread 1/4 cup sauce over two 12-inch pizza shells to within 1/4-inch of edge.
Sprinkle with the cheese and top with the onion. Bake 15 minutes or until the crust is golden brown. Makes 2 medium pizzas.

title: jello dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and add pie filling; let set. Frost with cream cheese and whipped topping.
May substitute different flavors of jello and pie filling.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a medium bowl, stir well. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl, toss gently and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: weight watchers fruit dip
directions: Mix together and serve with fruit.
Very good with apples and bananas.

title: dreamsicle fudge
directions: Cook butter, sugar and whipping cream over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to boil, cook and stir 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients in order and cook in a hot frying pan which has been well greased.
This mixture of dry ingredients may be premixed and stored in a glass jar.
Add eggs, milk and shortening when ready to serve.

title: beef stew
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cut beef into 1-inch chunks.
In large casserole, arrange beef, potatoes, onions, carrots and garlic. Pour beef broth and wine over it.
Add tomato paste and stir lightly.
Bury bay leaf and cloves.
Salt and pepper lightly.

title: orange dutch cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, butter, eggs and milk.
Add the sifted ingredients (flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt).
Mix thoroughly and add walnut meats, orange rind and raisins.
Bake in tube pan at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: incredi-bread!
directions: Dissolve yeast, water and sugar; set aside.
Mix together hot water and milk.
Combine milk, water, shortening, salt and sugar. Add 4 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add yeast.
Mix well and let rise for 45 minutes.
Add 2 more cups of flour; mix well.
Put remaining 1 cup of flour on breadboard and knead until all gone. Grease a large bowl.
Put the dough into the bowl and turn to grease dough.
Let rise 20 minutes.
Punch down.
Repeat 2 more times.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix together, put in refrigerator overnight.
Will keep for at least one week.

title: chocolate cake surprise
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of batter.
Bake as directed on package.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Pour first 3 ingredients in a saucepan and melt on low heat Let cool.
Mix in Cool Whip or whipping cream.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Chill and serve.

title: date balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and dates; stir well, then add egg. Cook mixture for about 4 minutes until ingredients stick together. Remove from heat and add cereal and nuts.
Cool; shape in walnut size balls.
Roll in coconut.
These can be frozen.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, covered.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and banana.
Sift flour and add to liquid mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour in a greased loaf pan.
Can double the ingredients and increase baking time slightly.

title: english biscuits
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the dry ingredients.
In a smaller bowl, combine the oil, milk and egg.
Quickly mix the wet and dry ingredients, stirring only until combined.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, marshmallows, celery, and walnuts.
Add enough salad dressing to moisten.
Toss lightly and chill.
May add additional dressing and garnish with apple slices before serving, if desired.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Peel and wash potatoes.
Slice round.
Chop onion; add salt and pepper to taste with 5 slices of butter.
Cook 15 minutes in microwave on High, stirring every 5 minutes.
Cook until tender.

title: zucchini omelet
directions: Mix eggs, Parmesan cheese, garlic, milk or water, salt and pepper.
Saute onion; add zucchini until mushy.
Combine all ingredients and pour in a skillet on medium heat.
When omelet is half cooked on one side, flip over and cook omelet until egg is cooked and cheese is melted.
Serve with crusty bread and garden fresh salad.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, milk and eggs.
Form balls.
Place in baking pan.
Combine other ingredients.
Pour over ham balls. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: drunken pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Season; add mixture of beer, catsup and brown sugar.
Let simmer, covered, for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: festive bean dip
directions: Spread in glass pie dish or similar container (I use jalapeno bean dip).

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Spray a large cold saucepan with Pam. Add celery, mushrooms, carrots, onion and garlic. Cook until tender.
Stir cut up drained tomatoes, sauce, Italian seasoning and sugar into vegetables. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes. Reduce to 2 cups.

title: western meal-in-one
directions: Brown ground meat until crumbly (if beef, pour off fat).
Add garlic, salt, onion, green pepper and chile powder and saute for 5 minutes or until veggies are limp.
Mix in tomatoes, beans and rice and turn into a 2 quart casserole.

title: bread and butter vegetable pickles
directions: Do not pare cucumbers; slice rather thin.
Add squash, onions, peppers and carrots with the cucumbers.
Pour 1/2 cup salt over the vegetables.
Cover with ice and ice water for 2 hours.
Drain well.
Do not rinse.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter snowballs
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, peanut butter and butter. Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: bud's sloppy joe's
directions: Brown meat, drain fat.
Add onion and green pepper and cook until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook uncovered over medium heat until mixture reaches desired consistency.
Serve on hamburger rolls.

title: divinity frosting
directions: Cook all ingredients in top of double boiler.
Beat with mixer while ingredients are cooking until it peaks.
Good on angel food cake.

title: appetizer ham rolls
directions: Slice intact rolls
in	half,
producing
split
halves (like 2
slices
bread).	Melt
butter;
add
Worcestershire, mustard, poppy seed and
onion.
Mix
well.	Spread on half of rolls with pastry brush.
Layer cheese and ham over this.
Top with other half of the rolls.	Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°,
taking
foil
off
at last 5 minutes. Slice each individual roll and serve warm.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serve warm or cold.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Bake 8 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: sauteed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini into 1/4-inch slices. Dip zucchini slices in egg. Coat with crumbs. In a frying pan, cook garlic in oil until brown. Cook zucchini slices until brown, turning once. Drain on absorbent paper. Serve immediately. Serves 6.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add cold water and cook until thick (3 to 5 minutes).
Remove from heat and add Jell-O, stirring until dissolved.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Add strawberries and topping.
This makes a 9-inch pie.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine sugars and oleo.
Add eggs and peanut butter; mix until creamy.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls and place on greased cookie sheets.
Flatten cookies with fork dipped in flour; crisscross.
Bake at 375° until set, but not hard.

title: cajun cucumbers
directions: Place sliced cucumbers in a bowl.
Add mayonnaise, as if making potato salad.
Add Cajun spice to taste.
Cover and shake.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix beans, peas, pimento, celery, green pepper and onion and a pinch of salt. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables. Let stand overnight. Makes 10 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients into a 6-cup baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes until beans are bubbly.

title: delicious salad
directions: Melt marshmallows and cheese in hot water.
Pour liquid over jello, then add pineapple juice.
When jello begins to congeal, fold in pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch rectangular dish.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: oyster fritters
directions: Add baking soda to oysters and mix well.
Add milk and then add flour and baking powder, sifted together.
Add salt and pepper and mix well.
Fry in an iron frying pan in plenty of hot oil.

title: hamburger pot roast
directions: Mix meat, eggs, 1 1/4 teaspoons salt, pepper, bread crumbs and milk.
Shape into a flat loaf.
Dredge with flour; brown on both sides in hot fat in a heavy skillet with a cover.
Add water and remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes, then add carrots and potatoes.
Cook 1/2 hour longer, or until carrots and potatoes are tender.

title: ham cheese quiche
directions: Rub pieces of meat well with salt and lay on board or table, skin side down.
Cover each piece with additional salt.
Leave meat in salt for 6 weeks.

title: angel food pie
directions: Combine sugar, pineapple and water in saucepan.
Add diluted cornstarch and cook until thick.
Whip 4 egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold hot mixture into beaten egg whites.
Pour into pie crust and chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, top with Cool Whip.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Stick cloves in onion.
Include all ingredients in a large pot and boil 50 minutes; drain.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Blend in flour.
Put
tomatoes
in
greased	casserole. Add rest of ingredients and 1/2 of the bread cubes.
Mix lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with rest of bread cubes and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Spread apples in square microwavable dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches. Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle evenly over apples.
Microwave on High (100%) 6 minutes; rotate dish 1/2 turn. Microwave until apples are tender, 6 to 8 minutes longer.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: garlic bread - a favorite!!
directions: In a small container soften butter or margarine.
Peel garlic; with a garlic press, press all 4 cloves, one at a time, into the softened butter mixture.
(Be sure to empty remaining garlic from the press into the mixture as well.) Mix well.
Butter Italian or French bread with mixture.
Wrap in aluminum foil and heat in oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Broil on high for 2 minutes if desired. Enjoy!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat potatoes with 1/2 stick oleo. Add sugar, milk and eggs. Pour into casserole dish. Combine 1/2 stick melted oleo, flour, chopped pecans, brown sugar and coconut. Pat mixture on top of potatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: soft drop sugar cookies
directions: Beat sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add melted Crisco.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk to mixture and blend.
To other 1/2 cup of buttermilk, add baking soda and stir until foamy, then add to mixture.
Beat well.
Add 2 cups flour with baking powder. Beat well, then add remaining 2 cups flour.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Drop rounded teaspoonful of mixture onto greased cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly brown.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: broccoli pasta salad
directions: Toss spaghetti with Italian dressing.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add mashed bananas, blending well.
Beat eggs one at a time into the mixture.
Add flour and soda that have been sifted.
Add nuts last.
Bake at 350° in a large pan for 25 minutes.

title: sugar pie
directions: Crumb together the brown and white sugars and flour in the pie crust.
Pour the milk and vanilla into the crust and mix with your fingers (this is important).
Dot top of pie with butter.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Shape mixture into small meatballs.
Melt shortening in frying pan and fry meatballs, turning often to brown on all sides.
If making in large quantities, cook in oven.
They may be cooked ahead and frozen.

title: orange ice tea
directions: Slice oranges into large bowl; add sugar and crush until sugar is dissolved.
Add water; crush again.
Let set for 15 minutes. Add to tea.
Add ice cubes.

title: parmesan dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Defrost and squeeze dry the spinach or greens.
Mix together 1 cup of the Parmesan cheese, the chopped spinach or turnip greens, onion, garlic, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Chop the optional red pepper and add to the mixture. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a greased casserole dish, top with the remaining Parmesan cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until hot and bubbly.
Freezes well, both before and after baking.
Serve with crackers.
Holds well in a chafing dish.
Makes 4 cups.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil until thickened; then set aside and cool.
Fold in the Cool Whip and drained mandarin oranges.
Chill.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk and set aside.
Cream butter and shortening; add sugar and beat until creamed.
Add egg yolks and mix thoroughly.
Stir in vanilla.
Alternately add flour and buttermilk mixture to butter mixture.
Stir in coconut and chopped pecans.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter. Divide batter between 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.
Test with toothpick.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Wash and drain zucchini.
Grind enough with the skin; remove all the seeds that you can.
Sprinkle zucchini, peppers and onions with salt.
Set aside overnight in refrigerator.
Place only in a glass, enamel or stainless steel bowl, do not use plastic or aluminum.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and spread wafer thin on a cookie sheet with sides.
Mixture will be thick.
Spread 1 egg white (unbeaten) over this and pour off excess.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped pecans with your fingers to cover completely.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Cut while hot in small squares or rectangles.

title: crunchy hot chicken salad
directions: Note:
I use 1/2 cup plain yogurt and 1/4 cup mayonnaise with the water.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown sausage and ground chuck in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add seasonings. Spread mixture onto rye bread.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until heated through.
Serve immediately.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Place in Dutch oven in order given.
Cook at 325° in oven for 1 or 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cabbage pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain.
Add flour and water. Stir.
Add cabbage.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add sour cream.
Stir.
Pour in crust and top with bacon. Put on top crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pretzel torte
directions: Crush pretzels by putting them in a plastic bag and pounding with the side of the rolling pin.
Pretzels should be crushed to about the size of coarsely chopped nuts.
Thoroughly cream sugar and butter.
Add pretzels; mix well with hands (mixture will be stiff).
Press mixture over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: paska(easter bread)
directions: Yeast Mixture:
Crumble yeast, 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/2 cup warm water.
Sift flour in pan, crack eggs and beat.
Put sugar in with flour and salt mixture.
Melt butter and heat milk.
Mix eggs with flour, salt, butter, milk and yeast mixture.
Let raise for 3 hours, then punch down.
Let raise again for another 2 hours, then cut it and put into pans.
Cover once again and let raise another hour.
Beat egg and put on top of bread.
Press with fork to get air out.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: american barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Stir in other ingredients. Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Can be refrigerated in covered container for 2 weeks.

title: delicious hot dish
directions: Brown
meat and drain off fat (add
celery
and
onions with meat)
when
browning.
Add
other	ingredients and bake 1 1/2 to 2
hours at 350°.
Do not add salt until you taste as soy sauce is salty.
Add more water if too dry (another cup or so).
(Do not precook rice or barley before mixing with meat.)

title: scrambled potatoes
directions: Begin by frying your meat.
Set aside for later.
Dice potatoes up in small pieces and fry.
Season to your liking.
When potatoes are almost done, dice your onion and tomatoes in the same small diced pieces and add to your potatoes.
Let simmer.

title: chicken pockets
directions: Blend cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk and chives; mix well.
Separate rolls into rectangles.
Seal 2 rolls together, shaping into a square.
Eight squares should be made.
Spoon meat mixture onto center (approximately 1/2 cup).
Pull 4 corners of dough to center and seal edges.
Brush top of each with melted margarine (1 tablespoon).
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes until puffed up and light brown. Freezes well.
My family loves this recipe!

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil carrots in salted water.
Drain and cool.
Cook vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, tomato soup and oil.
After cooking, add carrots, pepper and onion.
Cook 5 minutes.
Will last 3 weeks.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Combine cheese and sugar; mix well. Add egg yolks and blend thoroughly. Whip cream and add vanilla and salt. Beat egg whites stiff. Fold whip cream into cheese and egg mixture, then fold in egg whites. Spread 1/2 crackers on bottom of pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches. Pour in cheese mixture and put rest of crackers on top. Freeze. Serves 8.

title: candied carrots
directions: Scrape carrots and cut into strips.
Cook in boiling water 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Melt butter, sugar and allspice.
Stir until well blended.
Place carrots in baking dish. Pour sauce over and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chili
directions: In a large pan, brown ground beef with onion and chili powder, until the onion is translucent.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Cover and bring to a low boil.
Reduce heat; let simmer for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking or burning.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon in bag.
Place pieces of biscuits in bag and shake 1/3 at a time.
Place in greased Bundt pan.
Melt brown sugar and butter.
Pour 1/3 over biscuits.
Sprinkle 1/3 of nuts over top.
Repeat two more times.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: squash patties
directions: Cut up squash and boil in water until tender.
Take up and drain all the liquid out.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cut up a small onion in the squash.
Add egg, pinch of baking soda and enough flour to stick all together.

title: real lemon pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter, flour and 2 beaten egg yolks.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Add the Pet milk with 1/2 cup water slowly.
Fold in 2 beaten egg whites.
Turn into 1 (9-inch) unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: tea cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, soda, cream of tartar and butter; use 4 cups flour.
Knead well; roll thin and bake in 350° oven quickly.

title: broccoli parmesan
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in a little butter or margarine. Add lemon pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Stir in broccoli.
Serve over noodles.
Eat.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Wash unpeeled cuke and shred it.
Squeeze as much water out of cuke as you can so dip won't be too runny.
Mix all together. Serve with broccoli or cauliflower.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 1/2 gallon containers.
Freeze until needed.

title: onion-potato soup
directions: Cook onion and bacon drippings on low heat until tender (not brown).
Add potatoes, chicken soup, curry powder, water and salt. Cook until potatoes are tender.
Stir in milk, parsley flakes and crumbled bacon.
Heat through and serve.

title: ground beef and noodles casserole
directions: Mix two soups together.
Cook onion in beef.
Put a layer of each ingredient until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Put butter on top.

title: cornmeal pancakes
directions: Sift corn meal, flour and salt together.
Add 1 3/4 cups of the milk, butter and eggs.
Mix well; add soda, dissolved in rest of the milk.
Bake on a hot lightly greased griddle, turning to brown both sides.
Makes 6 pancakes.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla together until creamy.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend well.

title: brown betty(apple dish)
directions: Mix applesauce with cinnamon and sugar in 9-inch pie dish. Melt margarine and mix with bread crumbs.
Put over apples and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: play clay
directions: Mix, in saucepan, until thoroughly blended, cornstarch, baking soda and cold water.
Add a few drops of food coloring.
Cook over medium heat about 4 minutes, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens to moist mashed potato consistency.
Cover with damp cloth to cool.
Knead as you would dough.
Store in plastic container to keep from drying out.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions, put in casserole dish, then add other ingredients.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
Serve with tossed salad.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill in refrigerator.
Shape into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove and roll in powdered sugar, then roll in powdered sugar again.

title: layered strawberry jello
directions: Combine boiling water and Jell-O.
When dissolved, add thawed strawberries.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 of contents into 8 x 8-inch dish.
Refrigerate for 30 or 45 minutes.
When firm, spread sour cream on top.
Add remaining contents on top of sour cream and refrigerate.

title: fresh fruit dip #2
directions: *Apples, pears, pineapple, strawberries, grapes and melons can be used.

title: great grandma clark's chocolate caramels
directions: Thoroughly mix together almond paste, chocolate and almonds. Knead on surface sprinkled with 1 to 2 tablespoons of powdered sugar until of uniform color and consistency.
Shape into a roll about 6-inches long.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 12 hours.
Cut roll into 1/4-inch slices.
Makes 2 dozen candies.

title: quickie fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill well.
Mix well again before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Leave cake in pan and while it is still warm, punch holes in cake with a narrow steak knife.
Pour ice cream topping and Eagle Brand milk into cake.
Freeze toffee bars.
Break with hammer (wrapper on) into small pieces.
Thaw Cool Whip.
Spread on cake and sprinkle with toffee pieces.
Refrigerate.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Combine vanilla wafer crumbs, cocoa, powdered sugar, nuts, corn syrup and bourbon.
Shape into balls.
Roll in additional powdered sugar.
Makes 50 balls.

title: renegade party mix
directions: Mix together and put into a roasting pan.
Cover and bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Stir every 30 minutes.
Cool and put into an airtight container.

title: apple dip
directions: Blend together and serve with fresh apples or pears.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, vanilla and beat.
Add milk with 1 cup flour, sifted with baking powder; beat.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll out thin; cut and bake at 350° until done.
To decorate, sprinkle colored sugar or candies on top before putting in oven.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Blend egg whites, sugar, salt and vanilla in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water; beat with rotary beater, scraping bottom and side of pan occasionally until mixture forms peaks.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto 2 lightly greased baking sheets.
(Drop all mixture onto the 2 baking sheets; bake only 1 baking sheet at a time.)
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Immediately remove from baking sheet.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies, 20 calories each.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: easy, never fail fruitcake
directions: Blend together eggs, grape juice and date nut bread mix.
Add nuts and raisins.
Add candied fruit; mix well.
Grease and line tube pan or loaf pans with wax paper.
Fill 3/4 full and bake at 350° for 75 to 85 minutes for tube pan, 60 minutes for loaf pan.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Mix chicken broth and Ro-Tel.
Tear tortillas into small pieces and line a large baking dish with half of them.
Layer soup mixture, chicken, cheese, remaining tortilla pieces and onion. Top last layer with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Also freezes well.

title: sweet and spicy pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Mix in blender tomatoes, ketchup, dill weed, oregano and pepper.
Top pork chops with tomato mixture and simmer.
Add onions and simmer until chops are tender.

title: teriyaki for sirloin tips
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
If not tender, pound steak with meat mallet.
Center steak on aluminum foil of suitable size for each steak.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add 2 or 3 thin slices of onion and a dash or two of Worcestershire.
Wrap each steak tightly and bake for 4 hours.

title: reese's peanut butter squares
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate pieces; add milk.
Pour over peanut butter mixture.
Chill 20 minutes in refrigerator before cutting into squares.

title: caramel layered pie
directions: Prepare crust by mixing crumbs, sugar and 1 stick margarine. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: festive cheese ball
directions: Blend together cream cheese and bleu cheese, garlic, and pepper sauce in food processor or mixer.
Add shredded cheese. Mix well.
Shape into 2 medium or 1 large ball.
Chill until firm. Mix parsley and walnuts.
Roll chilled cheese balls in mixture until well covered.
Wrap in cellophane and keep chilled until ready to serve.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until creamy and light.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add oats, raisins and flour.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: casey's pretzel dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and dried beef together (use your hands). Add horseradish to taste.
This is a good dip for pretzels and crackers.
Allow to soften before serving.

title: uncle roys crab augratin
directions: Melt butter in sauce pan. Add crabmeat, mustard, egg and enough bread crumbs to hold mix together.
Salt & pepper to taste. Place mixture in ovenproof dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Cook under broiler until browned.

title: butter press cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Stir in flavorings.
Sift together flour and baking powder and stir in chilled dough.
Put through cookie press.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil on High for 2 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon soda and stir.
Put 4 1/2 to 5 quarts popped corn in a brown bag.
Pour mixture over corn and shake in paper bag.
Put bag in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Pour out in wax paper to cool.
May add nuts to popcorn before adding sugar mixture.

title: kody's chocolate cake(2001 ugliest cake winner)
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 can icing, and all other ingredients together. Bake at 350 degrees until done about 40 minutes.
Let cool and frost with other can of icing.

title: harvey wallbanger bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for cake, bake for 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing.

title: danish pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Beat butter and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add juice and rind.
Alternately stir in dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Stir in dates and nuts. Bake in Bundt or angel food cake pan at 350° for nearly 1 hour.
(Lightly grease and flour the pan.)
Pour the following sauce over the cake while hot.
Combine the grated orange rind rubbed into 1 cup sugar.
Heat until sugar is dissolved. For a moister pudding, double sauce recipe.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, mayonnaise, onion and cheese. Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole. Combine margarine and crackers and sprinkle over casserole to cover. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until topping is golden brown and casserole is bubbly.

title: fast turtles
directions: On wax paper, arrange nuts in groups of 4 and place one flattened caramel in the center of each group.
Place in microwave just until caramel softens and adheres to nuts.
Remove and cool. Melt chocolate and spoon over turtles and cool.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Select ribs and cut into serving pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in a roaster and cover with onions.
Make sauce by combining remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cover and bake in a moderate 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally and turn ribs once or twice.
Remove cover from roaster during the last 15 minutes to brown the ribs.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with 1/2 stick butter.
Press into 8-inch pie plate.
Saute onions until clear, but not brown, in 2 tablespoons butter.
Spoon into crust.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Cream together oleo, flour and sugar.
Alternate layers of fruit and mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: banana chocolate squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl of electric mixer at high speed, beat together shortening, sugars, egg, vanilla and salt until smooth.
Add bananas; mix well.
Add low speed, beat in flour and baking powder.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Spread in greased jellyroll tin.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until browned.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: empanadas
directions: In hot Crisco cook, not brown, chopped onions.
Add the meat once the onions are cooked and stir.
Do not cook the meat at this time.
(Take pan off stove.)
Add the condiments and set aside. Let cool this mixture a while.
Then add the chopped eggs and olives.

title: seasoned chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash and pat dry chicken breasts.
In plastic bag, combine bread crumbs, salt, flour, onion and garlic powder.
Add chicken, one piece at a time, shake and coat well. Place in hot frying pan with oil.
Brown on both sides.
When brown, place in baking dish.
Cover chicken with onion and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Mix until creamy.
Great over chocolate cake with Reese's cups chopped on top.

title: party fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add salt and pecans. Add flour, water and vanilla alternately. Shape into fingers or balls. Cook 30 to 40 minutes at 300° until lightly brown. Remove from cookie sheet and roll in powdered sugar.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: jogging-in-a-jug
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir to blend.
Chill.
Drink 6 ounces of mixture per day to lower cholesterol by as much and 20 points after 3 weeks!
Also gives many people added energy and pep!

title: chocolate zucchini sheet cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder, and salt; gradually add to the egg mixture alternately with the milk.
Stir in the zucchini and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 15 X 10 X 1-inch baking pan (jelly roll pan).
Bake at 375° degrees for 25 minutes, or until cake tests done.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips.
Spread on top and refrigerate.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan; press over bottom and 1 inch up sides to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
In small bowl, combine sour cream, horseradish, salt and pepper; blend until smooth.
Spread evenly over cooled crust.
Top with remaining pieces.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 60 appetizers.

title: amish pudding
directions: Combine dates, soda and boiling water and let cool.
Beat eggs, sugar, shortening, salt, flour and baking powder.
Combine with date mixture and fold in nuts.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh cream-style corn
directions: Mix all together and pour into large skillet.
Bring to boil; turn down heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: refried beans
directions: Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 3 hours.
Blend in a blender or food processor.
Tastes great!
Without fat!

title: garbanzo fritters
directions: Cook beans.
Mash beans and add other ingredients.
Fry in hot oil until golden.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Sift together remaining ingredients.
Blend the 2 mixtures.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Then roll in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
These cookies puff up at first, then flatten with a wrinkled top.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Add the 3 packages of sugar-free jello to the cottage cheese. Mix thoroughly.
Add well drained crushed pineapple and oranges. Mix well.
Add Cool Whip.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: easy pizza
directions: Spread sauce on bread and top with topping.
Add cheese and bake until bread is toasted and cheese melted.

title: layered casserole complete
directions: Cook meat until well done and drain.
You can add any of the following:
chopped onion, celery, bell pepper, garlic or mushrooms.
Add ketchup to meat mixture until consistency of Sloppy Joes.
Press into bottom of pan.
Layer drained green beans and prepared mashed potatoes.
Top with cheese and heat until cheese melts.
Serve with salad and bread.

title: ham barbecues
directions: Rub lettuce on skins of baking potatoes before placing them in oven.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Line buttered dish with rolls. Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Beat rest of ingredients and pour over sausage.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then serve.

title: wakee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake about 35 minutes in greased 9 x 11-inch cake pan.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, baking soda, and cinnamon.
Batter will be very thick.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Place in greased 9 x 13 inch pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until well browned.

title: italian style salad
directions: Wash and drain lettuce.
Tear into bite-sized pieces.
Mix in entire contents of the 2 jars of artichoke hearts.
After lettuce is well-coated, add fresh minced garlic, olives and onion slices. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Stir together eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla in a large mixing bowl. Stir in undrained pineapple. Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda. Add to pineapple mixture. Stir just until well combined. Stir in nuts. Pour batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack. Frost with your favorite cream cheese frosting and garnish, if desired.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter, marshmallow and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture has boiled 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate pieces, stir until melted.
Add vanilla and walnuts.
Turn into an 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.
Cut into squares when cool.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix and let set for 1/2 hour before rolling crust.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Saute hamburger and onion until done; drain off all fat.
Add remaining ingredients and heat.
Serve over buns.

title: jello delight
directions: Mix jello by box directions, then when the jello starts to gel, pour in pecans (chopped).
Then mix mayonnaise and Cool Whip together and use as the topping.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar and mix.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Pour into 2 loaf pans (greased).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mary ellen's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, reserving 1/2 of your diced cheese which you place over top of casserole.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan (divide into 2 pans) and place in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Bake 1 hour at 325° uncovered.
This casserole freezes well before baking.
I usually divide into 2 casseroles and bake one and freeze the other for a later meal.
This is very hearty and only needs the addition of a salad or green vegetable.

title: sour cream potato soup
directions: Saute bacon until crisp.
Add onions and leeks, saute until cooked.
Add flour and cook until thickened.
Slowly stir in bouillon.
Add potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are still a little hard (about 1 hour).
Stir frequently.
Combine sour cream and egg yolks.
Stir some of the soup into the mixture and then add to soup.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: best (except in a black skillet) cornbread
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Add eggs and mix lightly.
Add melted butter or margarine and mix well.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Pour batter in and cook in a preheated 375° oven for 25 minutes or until done.
Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: scratch coconut cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add milk, eggs, soda, vanilla and flour.
Beat at high speed for 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) cake pans (with flour and shortening).
Bake at 350° until done.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat together 2 minutes and then put in small foil bread pans, lightly greased.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Glaze while still warm.

title: seven layer taco dip
directions: In a 2-quart oblong casserole dish, spread the refried beans, jalapeno peppers and bean dip.
Sprinkle on the cheeses.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning and smooth on top of cheeses.
Gently pour the picante sauce over all.
(Recipe can be made ahead of time up to this point.)
Layer avocados, onions, tomatoes and black olives on top of casserole.
Serve with spoon for dipping onto tortilla chips.

title: brown sugar bars
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
In a medium bowl, combine the next 3 or 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add ingredients to large bowl.
Spread some butter in an ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes about 16.

title: spinach dip or sandwich spread
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on box and add a small amount of salt.
Drain spinach and press out all moisture.
Add vegetable soup mix to spinach.
Mix all other ingredients and add to spinach, mixing well.
Cover.
Place in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Freeze unused amount for later use.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Keep popped corn hot and crisp in low oven (300° to 325°). Melt caramels in water in double boiler, stirring frequently.
Add salt.
Place popped corn in large bowl and pour Caramel Sauce over. Toss to coat well.
Butter hands lightly; shape popcorn in balls.

title: hunter's cake
directions: Mix well first 4 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients. Beat all together well; then fold in 4 cups diced apples and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook cauliflower until tender; drain. Combine all ingredients, except cheese and butter.
Put in a large casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix first ingredients and top with Ritz crackers and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cook until very thick. Pour into baked pie shell. May top with meringue.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat milk to scalding; pour over bread crumbs.
Cool.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Set in pan of hot water 1 inch deep.
Bake until silver knife inserted in pudding comes out clean.
Bake 1 hour.
Serve warm.
Contains 290 calories.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar together for 3 minutes.
Add lemon Jell-O, dissolve well.
Then stir in cream cheese until all melted; let cool.
Add apples, celery, pecans and Cool Whip.
Put in dish to congeal and put in refrigerator to set.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: cantaloupe mousse
directions: Puree melon
to
equal
1 cup.
In top of double boiler, sprinkle
gelatin
over cold water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add melon when
cool.
Whip
cream until soft peaks form.
Whip egg whites until frothy, beat in sugar until stiff peaks form, fold cream
into
egg whites.
Add cantaloupe and gelatin mix.
Pour into serving
bowl.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Garnish with mint leaves.

title: coffee tortoni
directions: In a small mixer bowl at medium speed, beat egg white until foamy.
Add coffee powder and salt and beat at high speed until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in 2 tablespoons sugar until stiff peaks form.
In another small bowl at medium speed, beat cream until stiff.
Fold in almonds, 1/4 cup sugar, vanilla and almond extract just until combined.
Gently fold in egg white mixture. Spoon into six paper-cup lined muffin-pan cups or small dessert dishes.
Freeze at least 6 hours or overnight.
To serve, garnish each with a cherry half.
Can be eaten straight from the freezer. Makes 6 servings.

title: maria's meat balls
directions: Mix well and make small balls and drop in sauce raw.

title: mandarin orange and cashew chicken
directions: Reserving 2 tablespoons syrup, drain mandarin oranges.
Blend remaining syrup with fry sauce.
Heat oil in wok over high heat. Add chicken, cashews and garlic.
Stir-fry one minute.
Add onion and snow peas; cook to coat with sauce.
Remove from heat and stir in oranges.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Pour 1/4 to 1/2-inch of milk in glass baking dish with fish fillets.
Bake, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes, depending on thickness of fillets.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix everything together, except nuts.
Shape into a ball and chill 4 hours.
Roll in walnuts.

title: almond roca bars
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add egg yolk and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Pat dough in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned.
Immediately spread melted chips and add nuts.
Cut when cold.
Good for Christmas or for gifts.

title: grape and almond chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, grapes, celery and almonds in large bowl; toss to mix.
Add dressing.
Mix well.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, cook onion until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boil.
Add potatoes.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Partly cook frozen vegetables.
Cube potatoes.
Mix vegetables, soups and chicken.
Top with your favorite crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in closed container.
Use 1/3 cup of mix to 1 cup of hot water.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix and pour into baked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 or 50 minutes.

title: mother in law's turkey dressing
directions: Saute celery
and
onion
in margarine.
Cut up cooled, cooked chicken.
Mash
liver
and	chop gizzard.
In bowl, add seasonings.
Add
saute
mixture to bread.	Next, add meat and eggs.
Work in 2/3 cup broth.
Pat out mixture in baking dish. Pour 1/3 cup
broth on top.
Bake at 350° until done (about 45 minutes).

title: canola oil pie crust
directions: Mix together; divide dough in half.
Roll out between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Really works and is good.
Other oils could also be used.

title: flan
directions: Beat eggs until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour mixture into a well-buttered 1-quart baking dish.
Place dish in a large pan, which has been filled with just enough hot water to come up around baking dish.
Bake in a preheated oven (350°) for 1 hour or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Chill for several hours before serving. Serves 6.

title: mushroom quesadillas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a large skillet with vegetable oil. Cook mushrooms, onion and garlic in skillet over medium heat until onion is tender, about 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in cilantro and remove from heat. Arrange 1/3 of the mushroom mixture on half of 1 tortilla. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of the cheese. Fold the other half of the tortilla over the cheese. Place on a baking sheet. Repeat with the remaining ingredients to make 3 quesadillas total. Bake quesadillas about 5 minutes or until filling is hot and cheese melts. Cut each quesadilla into 4 wedges. Serve warm with salsa, if desired. Serves 6 (2 wedges per serving).

title: chicken curry
directions: Mix and pour over big chunks of chicken placed in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes until warm.
Can omit curry.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: biscuits(50 years old)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pat out on floured board or table.
Cut out and put in greased pan or skillet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.
(Can put melted bacon drippings in pan and put biscuits in and turn over to grease both sides.)

title: b.l.t. salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and then crumble bacon on top and cover with mayonnaise.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake 2 layer cakes (cool completely).
Prepare instant pudding according to package directions.

title: lumpia
directions: Wash vegetables and slice.
Peel shrimp and cut into halves. Slice round onion.
Saute pork and onion in 2 tablespoons oil. Add shrimp and cook until shrimp is reddish in color.
Add sliced vegetables, salt and ajinomoto to taste.
Cook on medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir well and set aside until cooled.
Wrap 1 tablespoon of mixture in a lumpia wrapper, folding wrapper to seal.
Fry each lumpia until golden brown.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water for 3 minutes. Add cake mix, 1 cup flour, eggs, oil and salt. Beat with mixer. Slowly add 5 1/4 cups flour and stir. Knead for 10 minutes. Let rise until doubled. Roll out 1/4-inch thickness. Spread with butter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Roll up jelly roll style and stretch. Cut into slices and place on pan. Let rise until double and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Ice with powdered sugar frosting.

title: coconut mounds
directions: Soften the margarine.
Add the coconut, powdered sugar, Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
Drop onto wax paper covered cookie sheets.
Refrigerate; roll into balls.
Refrigerate and dip.

title: potato casserole
directions: *You can use Monterey Jack and Colby mixture that you get already shredded at store.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown hamburger with chopped onion and pepper.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Layer into a 9 x 13 inch casserole dish--pinto beans, hamburger mixture, salsa, and jalapeno pepper.
Mix cheeses and layer on top.
Mix cornbread mix according to package directions.
Layer on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix together cheese, crabmeat, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and milk.
Put in oven to heat.
Heat until bubbly.
Serve covered with walnuts.
Yields 2 servings.
Prep time:
20 minutes.

title: dip for melon balls
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream together.
Chill.
Do not chill too deeply or dip will become too thick.
Serve with melon fruit balls.

title: cream of vegetable soup
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour; cook and stir until bubbly.
Gradually add chicken broth; cook and stir until thickened, about 5 minutes. Stir in the milk, cream, basil, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Add the vegetables; cook gently until heated through.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings (about 3 quarts).

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and add sugar and marshmallows.
Let this mixture set in refrigerator several hours, then fold in pineapple and whipped cream and serve.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Cut up chicken.
Cover with water and cook until tender. Cool.
Save broth.
Remove chicken from bone and cut into small pieces.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and mix.
Add 2 cups broth and cook until it thickens, stirring all the time.
Add cream and mix.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Stir together. Pour in a greased baking dish.
Cover.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
This is a good luncheon dish.

title: texas brownies
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour and sugar.
In saucepan, combine 1 stick of margarine, shortening, coffee or water and cocoa.
Stir and heat to boiling.
Pour boiling mixture over flour and sugar in bowl.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into a well-greased 17 1/2 x 11-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until test done in center. While brownies bake, prepare frosting.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine egg, peanut butter and sugar. Shape into 3/4-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Immediately press chocolate kiss in center of each cookie. Cool on a wire rack.

title: green beans a la spitzer
directions: In Dutch oven, brown the bacon crisp and remove onto paper towel.
Pour out some grease.
Keep the bottom of the Dutch oven covered with bacon grease.
Put in green beans, garlic and water chestnuts.
Let simmer awhile.
Add tomatoes.
If you use potatoes, put them in now.
Add olive oil.
Cook until potatoes are cooked to your liking.
Even the kids like green beans like this.

title: oakley's chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in 1/4 cup milk.
Add egg yolks and whip together.
Add rest of milk.
Put on heat until mixture begins to boil and add butter.
Let it cool and pour it into baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar and some vanilla. Spread it on top of pie and place it under the broiler until it turns golden brown.

title: chili
directions: Brown onions and ground beef.
In saucepan, cook spaghetti. Add ground beef mixture, tomato juice, kidney beans, chili hot beans and Chili-O mix powder.
Simmer until ready to eat.

title: honey butter
directions: Beat margarine and honey together until well blended.
Place in container in refrigerator until needed.
Use on pancakes, waffles, cornbread, biscuits and rolls.

title: sulfuring apples
directions: Beat the yoke of one egg; add one-fourth teaspoon each of salt and paprika and beat again, then use an egg beater and beat in two tablespoons of vinegar or lemon juice; beat vigorously, then add a teaspoon of olive oil and continue beating; add oil, a teaspoon at a time, three or four times, beating vigorously.
Meanwhile; then add the oil by the tablespoon until a cup in all has been used. Finish with one tablespoon of boiling water, beating it in, in the same manner as the oil.

title: apple cinnamon toast
directions: Use oven toaster or oven.
Slice apples.
Take bread and spread butter over it.
Place 5 to 6 slices of apples on bread. Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over apples.
Put into oven for about 5 to 8 minutes until apples are cooked and bread ends are toasty.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise, dig out pulp and saute it with ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Put mixture into bowl with
egg,	bread
crumbs
and
Parmesan
cheese.
Blend together. Put into
zucchini
shells.
Put spaghetti sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch
pan,
lay
zucchini
on
top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Put Mozzarella cheese on top of squash a few minutes before finished baking.
Serve with spaghetti noodles or rice.

title: jim's low-fat crab soup
directions: Add celery soup to (picked over for shells) crabmeat.
Stir together and heat well.
Add 1 teaspoon sherry to each serving or can add 1 teaspoon lemon juice instead.
Can stir in 1 cup of skim milk to mixture if too thick for your taste.

title: perfect chicken roaster
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in large size (14 x 20-inch) Reynolds oven cooking bag; place bag in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place onion and celery in bag.
Rinse chicken; drain and pat dry.
Tie legs together with string and tuck wing tips under chicken.
Brush chicken with oil; sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place chicken in bag.
Close bag with nylon tie; make 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top.
Insert meat thermometer through slit in bag into center of thigh, next to body, but not touching bone.
Bake 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 180°.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry slush bucket
directions: In blender, combine 1 package of strawberries, 1 can lemonade, 3/4 cup water and 3/4 cup ice.
Cover and blend smooth.
Pour into a non-metal freezing container and repeat with remaining ingredients.
Freeze overnight and 2 hours before serving; let stand at room temperature until slushy.
Add club soda and stir gently.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.
Makes 24 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: old-fashioned ambrosia
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover mixture and chill for at least 8 hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef and biscuits
directions: Chop onion and green pepper.
Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt. Shred cheese.
Slightly beat egg and combine with 1/2 cup cheese and sour cream.
Remove meat from heat and stir in cheese mixture.

title: sourdough starter (herman)
directions: Stirring as little as possible, combine 2 cups flour and yeast with lukewarm water, to make a thick batter.
Let stand 24 hours, then stir in 1/2 cup sugar, 1 cup milk and 1 cup flour. Stir once a day for the two following days.

title: chicken-noodle casserole
directions: Grease a large shallow casserole.
Place layer of chicken, then noodles.
Mix soup and chicken stock together; pour over noodles.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until bubbly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: raisin pie
directions: Let raisins boil until tender; drain.
Add to custard which has been cooked.
Place in baked pie crust and cover with meringue.

title: zucchini drop cookies
directions: Combine squash, sugar and oil and mix well.
Add beaten egg and mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Combine flour mixture to squash mixture and mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger with onion added.
Drain grease; add other ingredients.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375°
for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together except egg whites.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into filling mixture.
Pour into 1 large pie shell or 2 small pie shells.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: peach crisp
directions: Mix sugar, oatmeal, flour and cinnamon.
Work margarine into dry ingredients with fingers.
Slice peaches in 10 x 7 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour flavored water over peaches.
Sprinkle flour mixture over top.
Bake at 350° until light brown, about 45 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: honey orange carrots
directions: Put all items in a saucepan.
Cook until carrots are tender. Stir in parsley last.

title: easy bake cheesecake
directions: Combine sugar, cream cheese, lemon juice, salt and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Beat eggs into mixture, one at a time.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Chill before serving.
Add favorite fruit topping.
(May divide filling and make 2 pies.)

title: sweet potato bread with pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine sugar, water, oil, eggs and sweet potatoes and mix thoroughly. Add dry ingredients and mix to combine. Add pecans and mix well. Divide between 2 greased loaf pans and bake for 50 minutes. Cool in pan to room temperature.

title: stuffed zucchini squash
directions: Wash and trim stem end of squash.
Cut in half lengthwise. Cook in boiling water 10 minutes.
Drain.
When cool enough to handle, scoop out center of each.
Drain shells upside down.
Chop scooped portion.
Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add chopped zucchini and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into shells and arrange in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple-walnut bread(2 loaves)
directions: Beat eggs with sugar; add oil, salt, cinnamon and vanilla. Stir in flour, baking soda, apples and nuts. Dough will be very thick. Place in 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until center tests done. Makes about 12 to 16 servings.

title: german tomato and egg salad
directions: Combine boiled eggs, onion, pickles and cheese.
Use amounts according to servings.
Chop eggs, pickles and onion.
Cut up cheese.
Combine with mayonnaise; put on bread slices.
You may want to add chopped ham or bacon bits.
Broil until cheese is melted and toast is brown.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Cook bacon crisp and crumble.
Cook onion in bacon fat.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper, chives or parsley and cooked onion together.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle bacon and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until real firm.

title: dip for fresh veggies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let set for several hours or overnight.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack okra; add dill, garlic, pepper and alum.
Mix vinegar; bring to boil.
Pour over okra.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream; pour over and fold.
Sprinkle cheese over the top.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart casserole, sprinkle a few of the crumbs on the bottom.
Spread layer of mixed fruit and nuts, followed by another layer of cookie crumbs.
Repeat this procedure, ending with a layer of cookie crumbs.
Pour in sherry and cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Brown ground beef in a large iron skillet. Drain.
Return beef to skillet and add taco seasoning mix, tomatoes
and	corn.
Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat, stirring
occasionally.
Beat
egg in small mixing bowl. Add milk
and
cornbread mix.
Stir until smooth.
Spoon cornbread batter
over ground beef mixture. Bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in bottom of a baking dish. Pour water over them.
Combine all other ingredients and put on top of apples.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese ring
directions: Combine cheeses, onion, mayonnaise and red pepper and mix well. Sprinkle about 1/4 cup pecans in an oiled 7-cup ring mold and press cheese mixture into
mold.
Chill until firm.

title: lemon-angel bars
directions: Combine cake mix and pie filling.
Stir until well blended. Spread into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; cool.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients together with your mixer, as this will break up your oranges.
Put into containers and chill.
Serves: 10.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When cool, frost with cream cheese icing.

title: juanita's drop biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together twice.
Using two knives, cut shortening into flour mixture until well mixed.
Add buttermilk; stir well.
Drop level tablespoonfuls of dough onto greased cookie sheet.
Place a pat of butter on each biscuit.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Yields 26 biscuits.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients as you would for regular cornbread.
Pour into greased pans, will make a large amount.
Don't get it too thick or it will not get done in the center.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Place beans, tomato juice, onion, garlic, cumin and cayenne pepper in a food processor or blender and puree.
Serve with crackers or vegetable sticks.
Yields 8 servings (1/4 cup each).

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Pour
boiling
water (salted) over broccoli.
Cover and let stand.
Saute celery, onion and butter.
Mix all together. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese baked chicken breasts
directions: Remove any bones or skin from breasts.
Rinse, pat dry and arrange chicken in 2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Place slices of cheese over chicken.
Stir soup and wine together and pour over.
Coarsely crush stuffing mix and sprinkle over and evenly drizzle on butter.
Sprinkle top generously with paprika.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
A rich cheese sauce forms while baking.
Serve with rice if desired.

title: peachy pecan bread
directions: Finely chop 1 cup peaches and set aside.
In blender, combine remaining peaches, butter, eggs, syrup and lemon juice.
Blend until smooth.
Stir dry ingredients together.
Add egg mixture and stir until moist.
Fold in reserved peaches and nuts.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Cut green chilies in half.
Divide Jack cheese strips evenly among chile strips arranged in bottom of greased shallow pan. Beat eggs until thick and foamy, add milk, flour and baking powder, beat until as smooth as possible.
Pour batter over chilies and cheese strips, sprinkle with sharp Cheddar and bake, uncovered, at 375° for about 30 minutes or until set.
Garnish with mild salsa over top and sliced olives, if desired.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: refrigerated chocolate cream pie
directions: Bake 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain some juice from the pork and beans.
Mix together all ingredients, except the bacon.
Crumble the bacon on top.
Bake in a covered casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sauce for ham
directions: Strain drippings and measure.
Add white wine and bring to boil.
Serve with ham.
Makes 12 servings.

title: tomato fig
directions: Place tomatoes in salt brine for 2 hours.
Drain and rinse. Cook tomatoes and raisins with sugar, vinegar, cloves and cinnamon until thick.
This will keep without sealing.
Serve with cold roast beef or pork.

title: chocolate layer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Mix flour and dry ingredients, then add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Stir in flavoring.
Bake in 4 layers at 375° until done.

title: marmalade - with pectin
directions: Remove mandarin and lemon peels, lay peel flat, cut off as much of the white part of the peel as possible, discard white.
Slice the peel into very thin slices.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups water, bring to a boil and simmer for 20 minutes.
Chop the fruit pulp and discard any seeds and membrane.
Add pulp to undrained peel and simmer for 10 minutes.
Measure 3 cups of the fruit into a kettle and mix in sugar.
Follow procedure on pectin container for the rest of the processing.
Skim foam off top and ladle into hot, sterilized glasses, seal.
Makes seven 8 ounce glasses.

title: layered salad
directions: Place in layers in large flat dish in order given.
Place bacon on top.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
Spoon out servings.
Do not toss.
Will keep in refrigerator 2 or 3 days.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cavalier cake
directions: Melt morsels over hot water and set aside to cool.
Sift together flour,
baking powder and salt; set aside.
Blend shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks, 1 at a time, with vanilla and melted chocolate.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into batter.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at around 350°.
This cake will come out in 40 minutes.
Ice with your favorite homemade chocolate icing.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; set aside.
Beat eggs; beat in oil and vanilla.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Stir dry ingredients into egg mixture, alternating with apple mixture. Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into greased Bundt pan or oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Cook the flour, sugar, vinegar, egg and pineapple until thick (like pudding).
Cool and refrigerate overnight.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add nuts, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Hand stir in the apples.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch cake tin (greased and floured).
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 X 13 pan.
Mix chopped pecans and coconut and put in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to package directions and pour over pecans and coconut.
Cream margarine and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cake mixture in pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: cream cake
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, cream and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and stir only to blend.
Put in greased pan.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.
This is very good to use for strawberry short cake.

title: beef hash
directions: Preheat broiler.
In food processor, process meat until coarsely chopped, about 1 minute.
Transfer to medium bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape mixture into 4 patties and place on nonstick baking sheet.
Broil the patties 4 inches from the heat for 6 to 8 minutes on each side until crisp and golden.

title: dee's coke cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Melt and bring to a boil butter, buttermilk and cocoa.
Mix together coke, eggs and vanilla.
