Pour melted cocoa mixture over flour mixture, then add coke mixture.
Pour into sheet cake pan and bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes.
Frost while cake is still warm.

title: jo's hush puppies
directions: In a medium bowl, add cornmeal mix, egg, onion, corn, salt and sugar.
Add buttermilk until mixture is thickened.
Let sit for 5 minutes and stir again.
Mixture should hold together when formed into balls or shaped into "hush puppies" with 2 teaspoons. Drop into hot grease.
Hush puppies will float.
Turn when browned on underside.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: mexican combo
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper in a large skillet.
Mix chili powder and water; pour over meat mixture.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add cheese, beans with juice, salt and pepper.
Simmer until cheese melts being careful not to let scorch.

title: aunt adeline's apple cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; mix well and set aside.
In second bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Combine well.
In smaller bowl, mix the eggs, oil, vanilla and juice. Combine wet and dry ingredients.
Fold in apple mixture.
Bake in ungreased tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Let the cake stand before removing from pan.
If necessary, dust with powdered sugar of "drizzle" thinned icing over the top before serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: russian chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Heat.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Arrange ribs in shallow baking dish or pan. Combine soy sauce, teriyaki sauce and liquid from pineapple chunks.
Reserve chunks. Add garlic.
Drizzle half sauce over marinade ribs.
Prebake ribs at 350° for about 30 minutes; turn over 15 to 20 minutes baking, basting with sauce in pan.
Pour juices from pan into remaining sauce marinade.
Place pan with ribs on rack.
Baste ribs with sauce.
Sprinkle with pepper and ginger.
Broil for about 15 minutes, basting with sauce and turning ribs from time to time, until they are glazed and tendered.
Add pineapple chunks and broil another 5 minutes.
Steam or boil pea pods just until tender-crisp, about 3 minutes, and serve.

title: fruit and nut carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix oil, sugar, eggs, beating after each addition.
Add dry ingredients, mix well.
Blend in carrots, pineapple, nuts and raisins.
Grease and flour 9x13x2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 min.

title: english pear pie
directions: Crumble English muffins and set aside.
Drain and chop pears into small pieces and place in 9-inch or 10-inch pie plate sprayed with Pam.
In processor or blender, mix lemon juice, eggs and sugar.
Add milk and mix, then add English muffin crumbs.
Pour over pears.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool and place on plate.
In pan, melt margarine and add brown sugar and cream. Bring to boil 4 to 5 minutes.
Turn fire off and add vanilla.
To serve, spread Cool Whip on top and pour sauce over.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, milk and pepper.
In casserole dish arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion, soup and cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: grilled cheese pizza
directions: Place a slice of cheese between two slices of bread and spread the sauce over the cheese.
Cook it like you would a grilled cheese sandwich.

title: roast potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Coat bottom of cookie sheet with 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Set aside.
Wash potatoes but do not peel! Cut in 1/4-inch chunks (steak fry size).
Mix with remaining ingredients and spread out on a cookie sheet.
Cook until brown and crisp.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Pour milk in large bowl. Add pudding mixes. Beat with whisk 30 seconds. Add lemonade. Beat 30 seconds more (mixture will be thick). Stir in whipped topping. Spoon into baked crust. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Garnish with lemon slices, if desired. Store leftover pie in refrigerator.

title: sweet-and-sour red cabbage(servings: 6)
directions: Melt butter in 4-quart Dutch oven.
Add apples and onions; saute slightly.
Add finely shredded cabbage, red wine, cloves, sugar and bay leaves.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour, then add the remaining ingredients.
Heat to melt the butter and serve immediately.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and vanilla gradually.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. These cookies store well.
Can be baked 2 or 3 days ahead.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Cut oleo into 3/4 cup flour, then add rest of the flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in milk.
Dough should be stiff enough to pull away from the sides into a ball.
Place on a floured surface and knead at least 10 times.
Roll or pat to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with a biscuit cutter or 2-inch round glass.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.

title: pollo-chili verde a la americana
directions: Cut chicken up and boil in pan until done.
(You may add poultry seasoning to the water while cooking for better flavor.) Let chicken cool, then remove skin and remove from bone.
Shred chicken to desired size.
Start to layer the crock-pot with tortillas, then chicken and cheese.
Add a little sauce on top. Continue to layer until all ingredients are gone.
Make sure you finish top layer with cheese.
Pour excess sauce on top.
Turn crock-pot to high; cook until cheese is melted and simmering. Cooking time: approximately 2 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, nuts, coconut and cherries.
Top with pineapple.
Add water to juice to measure specified liquid on cake mix box.
Prepare as directed on package. Spread evenly over fruit mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until test done.
Cool 5 minutes; invert onto large serving dish.

title: quick cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan until blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: snowball dessert
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cake.
Refrigerate until semi-set.
Then tear cake into little chunks.
Using part of cake chunks, make a layer of cake in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Spoon half of mixture (gelatin) over cake.
Repeat with cake and mixture until all is gone.

title: weight watchers corn bread
directions: Bake at 400° until brown.
Makes 2 servings.
Per serving:
1 br, 1/2 m, 1 1/2 f, 15 opt. cal.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook bacon in frying pan until crisp.
Remove and reserve. Add butter, onions, celery and green pepper to grease in pan; saute until tender.
Transfer to a large pot, along with the fried bacon.
Add all other ingredients, except the shrimp, saltines and sherry.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours, until mixture thickens.
Add shrimp and cook until done.
If using raw shrimp, cook about 10 to 15 minutes.
If using frozen shrimp, precook, following package directions.
Add crushed saltines and sherry.
Serves 8 to 10 generously.

title: stuffed cheese bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except French bread, well by hand.
Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Remove some bread from middle and spread with butter.
Put filling in middle of both halves of bread.
Put together.
Wrap tightly with Saran Wrap and foil. Refrigerate overnight.
Slice to serve.

title: a man loving casserole
directions: Cook hamburger until all redness is gone.
Slice potatoes and onion thin and place in a greased casserole dish.
Add hamburger and seasonings.
Spoon out Cheddar cheese soup, covering the hamburger.
Add water, cover and cook 50 minutes at 325°.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with assortment of raw vegetables.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli following package directions.
Melt butter.
Add crushed Ritz crackers; mix well.
Set aside.
Mix broccoli, shredded cheese, soup and beaten eggs.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Pour broccoli mixture into dish and top with crushed crackers.
Place dish in pan of water and cook for 1 hour on 300°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Pile lightly into a casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pin candy
directions: Beat and cook together first 5 ingredients until soft ball forms in cold water.
Set aside to cool.
Stir well until light in color.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Turn on buttered plates and cut while warm.

title: split pea soup
directions: Heat water and peas to boiling in a Dutch oven; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Coat fresh drained blueberries with powdered sugar.
Place in baked pie shell.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick and pour over pie.

title: taco bake
directions: Preheat oven to temperature designated on tube of crescent rolls. Line bottom of 9 x 13 inch baking dish with one tube of crescent rolls and place in oven for 5 minutes. While this is baking,

place hamburger in frying pan and cook until brown, then drain. Add taco seasoning according to the package directions. Add jar of salsa con queso to hamburger and stir. Layer evenly over top of crescent rolls. Open second tube of crescent rolls and layer over hamburger. Place in oven until crescent top is golden brown (around 15 minutes).

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger and combine with package of taco seasoning mix.
Set aside.
Toss together the lettuce, onion, tomatoes, cheddar cheese, and kidney beans.
Add the hamburger mixture. Just before serving, add nacho chips and Catalina dressing.
Mix well.

title: country corn
directions: Cook onion and bell pepper in 2 tablespoons margarine for about 5 minutes.
Add flour, paprika, mustard, salt and milk. Heat until bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in corn and egg. Pour in a 1-quart casserole, mixing in the Cheddar cheese.
Mix the bread crumbs in the 1 tablespoon margarine and place on top of corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: super seashell salad
directions: Cook seashells according to package directions.
Drain well. Cool.
Rinse with cold water to cool quickly.
Drain well.

title: whole peach pie
directions: Wrap peaches in squares of pie crust.
Bake on cookie sheet at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with warm sauce.

title: old fashioned sugar cream pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour, and salt. Pour one-half of mixture into the unbaked pie shell.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut broccoli into pieces.
Should have about 4 cups.
Bring salted water to a boil.
Add pasta to water.
Cook about 3 minutes. Add broccoli and boil about 8 minutes or until tender.
Drain and add butter and cream and toss.
Add cheese and salt, if needed.

title: seven layer salad
directions: This salad requires layering from the bottom to the top.
It's very colorful when made in a large glass bowl.

title: cheese and bacon sandwiches
directions: Spread 1 side of bread with Cheez Whiz.
Cut bacon into small pieces and place over Cheez Whiz.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until cheese is golden brown and bacon is cooked.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients.
Add oil.
Beat eggs.
Blend in pineapple and vanilla.
Pour into flour mixture.
Add chopped nuts. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Frost with:

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef; add onion and pepper.
Drain fat and add tomato soup.
Rinse can with about 1/2 water and add to mixture.
Cook on low and add noodles and cook until noodles are tender.
Pour in casserole dish and top with grated cheese or Mozzarella cheese. Put in oven until cheese melts.

title: quick sticky buns
directions: Combine ingredients; put in a cake pan.
Top with the 10 refrigerator biscuits.
Bake as directed on package, or until golden brown.

title: danish spaghetti
directions: Fry onion in a little butter until transparent.
Add sausage, chicken, ham, spinach, mushrooms, tomato sauce and chili powder to drained spaghetti.
Add some broth and then add cheese, that you have cut into small chunks.
Add more broth as needed to make to mixture pretty soupy.
Butter casserole and bake at 325° 10 to 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan over very low heat, melt morsels and butter, stirring occasionally until well blended. (I use microwave.)
Add baking mix, condensed milk and egg.
Stir well.
Stir in nuts.
Spray or lightly grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour mixture into dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cut into squares.

title: banana split pie
directions: In the graham cracker crust, layer the remaining ingredients. Freeze.
Serve with chocolate sauce drizzled over top.

title: cream potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes and slice onions.
Cook potatoes and onions in water until tender.
Remove onions and stir in milk.
Bring to boiling point.
Remove from fire and serve.

title: daiquiri cocktail
directions: Shake well with cracked ice and strain into 3 ounce cocktail glass.

title: overnight chili sauce
directions: Remove skins and chop or grind the tomatoes.
Add onions and peppers.
Mix with salt and let stand overnight.
In morning, drain in colander or cheesecloth for 2 hours.
Add vinegar, spices and sugar.
Boil quickly until thick, then pour into jars and seal.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix together and chill before serving.

title: broccoli salad supreme
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Prepare broccoli flowerets.
Crumble crisp bacon strips.
Add to first ingredients.
Mix, cover and refrigerate about 1 hour or longer.
Enjoy!

title: creamed cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Cook and drain broccoli (save juice) and mix with chicken broth.
Cook 5 minutes.
Mix flour and melted butter; add to soup mixture.
Add broccoli and cheese.
Stir until blended.

title: shrimp du chef
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter; saute onion and garlic until tender.
Add shrimp, mushrooms, beef broth and lemon juice; saute 2 minutes.
Add wine and parsley.
Heat through.
Season to taste with salt and white pepper.
Remove shrimp from sauce and arrange on plates.
Cook sauce 1 minute longer and pour over shrimp. Garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 appetizers or 2 entree servings.

title: sugar-raisin cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in water to barely cover until water is all absorbed.
Set aside to cool.
Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Sift together the dry ingredients, except last sugar, and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins. Roll dough into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place balls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Flatten with bottom of sugar-dipped glass.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, until lightly browned.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: banana milkshake no. 2
directions: Blend all ingredients, except ice cubes, in blender container. Add ice cubes, one at a time, and process after each addition. Makes 2 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine and cook first two ingredients to a soft ball stage. Add vanilla and stir.
Add peanut butter, stir and pour into pan.

title: golden cheese hash browns
directions: Mix all well; put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed crackers or breadcrumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry nut loaf
directions: Preheat
oven
Sift together in a mixing bowl the flour,
sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Stir in the orange juice,
rind,
shortening
and
egg.
Mix
until
well blended. Stir
in
chopped cranberries and nuts.
Turn into a greased
x 5-inch
pan.
Bake
for
55 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted into the center comes out clean.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: date balls
directions: Cook dates, oleo, egg yolks, sugar and vanilla in a heavy iron pan, over low heat, until dates dissolve.
Cool 10 minutes; add Rice Krispies and pecans.
Cool until mixture can be handled.
Roll into small balls, then roll in coconut.

title: apricot bars
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and apricots.
Add melted butter.
Put 3/4 of mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with apricots; top with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool, cut and serve.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except noodles.
Place in casserole. Bake at 450° (preheat oven) for 7 1/2 minutes, then spread noodles over top of casserole and bake 7 1/2 minutes longer.
Do not cook longer than 15 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk, and evaporated milk until creamy. Add sugar and cream cheese; mix well. Add Cool Whip and stir until well mixed. Place layers starting with a layer of cookies, bananas, and pudding mixture. Makes a large banana pudding.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Place beef on rack in roasting pan.
Put into unheated oven and heat oven to 500°.
Roast beef for 5 minutes for each pound of weight (roast a 4 pound roast for 20 minutes).
Turn off oven.
Do not open door.
Leave beef in oven for 2 hours.
Remove from oven; let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: cool rise sweet dough
directions: Measure flour and set aside.
Sprinkle
yeast into warm water and
stir.
Add
warm
milk, sugar, salt, margarine and eggs.
Mix well
and
add flour, 1 cup at a time, until dough pulls
away from bowl. Turn onto floured bowl and knead for 5 minutes.
Cover with
towel
and
leave
in
warm area for 20 minutes.
Punch down and make into rolls or loaves.
Allow to rise
for
2 hours. (May be left in refrigerator for 48 hours before
shaping.)
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen rolls or 2 loaves.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil eggs for 15 to 20 minutes.
Put water in saucepan and add salt.
Heat until boiling.
Put peeled potatoes in boiling water. Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Wash other veggies.
Trim and slice. Add mayonnaise, mustard, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Mix well. Cube potatoes.
Add to mayonnaise mixture.
Peel and cut eggs. Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: mystery pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
When cool, add Dream Whip for topping.

title: beet pickles
directions: Heat and pour over hot beets in hot jar.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans well.
Mix all ingredients.
Put salad in flat, low dish.
This salad is better if made the day before serving. It keeps well in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: sticky buns
directions: Add sugar, salt and oleo to hot potatoes.
When warm, add yeast, eggs and potato water. Stir in flour to make stiff dough. Knead well until smooth.
Put in greased bowl and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and put in refrigerator until chilled (may be kept in refrigerator for several days). Butter Pyrex or aluminum pans well.
Cover bottom with 1/3-inch brown sugar. Add enough water to make sugar wet.
Sprinkle with nuts. Roll dough about 1/2-inch thick.
Brush with butter. Sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Roll like jelly roll.
Cut in 1/2-inch circles.
Place cut side down in sugar and let rise double in size.
Bake at 350°.
Invert pan on plate while hot or it will stick.

title: tv treat
directions: Melt butter and mix Worcestershire sauce and onion salt.
Set aside.
Put cereal and cashews in large roaster pan.
Pour mixture over cereal.
Put in a 250° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Mix lightly every 1/2 hour.

title: david beattie's salad
directions: Peel cucumbers if waxed.
Cut into cubes.
Chop onion, pepper and tomatoes.
In a medium bowl, mix all ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: nutty holiday popcorn
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Place popcorn and peanuts in 2 ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pans.
In medium saucepan, combine margarine, sugar, gelatin, water and corn syrup.
Cover over medium-low heat until sugar and gelatin dissolve, stirring constantly.
Using candy thermometer, continue cooking to 255° (Fahrenheit, hard ball stage), stirring constantly.
Pour syrup over popcorn and peanuts; stir to coat.
(Mixture will be hot.)

title: double chocolate fantasy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, oil and egg.
Beat on medium speed until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Reserving 1 1/2 cups of crumb mixture, press remainder on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 20 minutes.
An alternative may be to cover beans and cook in microwave for 12 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes.

title: pheasant en creme(adaptable for chicken)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place pheasant in ungreased baking dish, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix soup, cider, Worcestershire sauce, salt, onion, garlic, mushrooms and wine.
Pour over pheasant.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Basting occasionally, bake uncovered, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
(May substitute a 2 pound chicken or 4 filleted breasts of chicken, reduce time to 1 hour for fillets.)

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix together. Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Microwave broccoli and cauliflower or steam until tender. Blend remaining ingredients together.
Combine vegetables and sauce; sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry ice cream pie 1
directions: Combine gelatin and hot water in a mixing bowl and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in the pint of ice cream until melted. Beat mixture thoroughly by hand or with electric beater until light and fluffy.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover top with aluminum foil and refrigerate 4 hours. Just before serving, whip the cream with confectioners sugar and spread over pie.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour into 3 cake pans and cook as directed.
After cake layers are completely cooled, split all 3 layers in half.

title: christmas candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Boil until it forms hard crack stage when tested in water.
Remove from heat and add cinnamon oil and food coloring.
Pour on cookie sheet that's been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
After mixture is cooled, break into small pieces with a spoon.

title: bulgogi
directions: Combine ingredients and stir-fry.

title: ham steak with raisins
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine water and cornstarch.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except ham, and microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until sauce is thick.
Stir once every minute.
Set aside.
Place ham in baking dish.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes, turning over once after half the time.
Pour sauce on ham.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for 2 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix 3 teaspoons per cup water and serve.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Grease or Pam 1-quart casserole.
Place pineapple chunks in casserole.
Mix sugar, flour and pineapple juice and pour over pineapple chunks.
Spread cheese over mixture.
Melt butter and mix into cracker crumbs.
Put over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lime pickles
directions: Let cucumbers soak 24 hours.
Wash 3 times and let soak 3 hours.
Mix
vinegar and add other ingredients.
Drain pickles; pour
on
vinegar
mix and let stand overnight.
Boil 35 minutes. Makes around 10 pints.
May add green cake coloring, if desired.

title: best carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°. Beat the margarine, brown sugar and white sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat until light.
Combine juices and peels; add to creamed mixture.
Beat in flour mixture in quarters.
Fold in carrots, nuts and raisins.
Bake for 60 minutes, or until pick comes out clean.
Frost with cream cheese frosting, or dust with powdered sugar.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and salt. Add the beaten eggs, milk and margarine. Stir well. Add the coconut. Bake in pie shell at 350° until brown and set in the middle.

title: gob cake
directions: Mix cake per directions on the box; add pudding and egg yolks. Beat for 5 minutes.
Spread into 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans lined with wax paper.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°; remove and let cool. Put Icing between cakes and refrigerate.

title: beef wiener wraps
directions: You also need toothpicks and crock-pot.

title: porcupines
directions: In a bowl, blend peanut butter, condensed milk and confectioners sugar together thoroughly with a wooden spoon, then knead with your hands.
Divide candy mixture into small pieces. Roll each piece into ball about 1-inch in diameter, then roll candy balls in chopped peanuts.

title: hamburger and rice casserolefort morgan, colorado
directions: Brown ground beef and add chopped onions and celery.
Add salt and pepper and Cream of Mushroom soup and cook until well mixed.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until soft ball forms when tested in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate bits and marshmallow.
Stir until combined.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool; cut into blocks.
Nuts may be added same time as marshmallows. Makes about 5 pounds.

title: nanna's crazy coconut custard pie
directions: Blend all but coconut in blender for 2 minutes.
Stir coconut. Pour in 10-inch glass fluted pie pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: tapi-orange salad
directions: Combine pudding mixes, Jell-O, water and juice.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Cool completely.
Fold in oranges, pineapple and whipped topping.
Chill.

title: easy rolled-oat scones
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening with two knives or pastry blender-or short on-off strokes- in blender, until crumbly.
Add milk to make soft dough.
Roll dough out on floured board to about 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut into triangles and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with fruit spread or apple butter.

title: 15 minute cookies
directions: Mix and measure 2 cups mixture into 6 freezer bags. When ready to bake cookies, add 1 egg and 1/2 cup butter flavored Crisco to one of the bags. Mix. Dampen fingers and roll into walnut sized balls. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 18 to 24 cookies.

title: banana muffins
directions: Combine margarine and sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in bananas.
Combine flour and soda. Add to creamed mixture.
Fill muffin pan 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken in 6 cups water.
Let cool and cut into small pieces (deboned and fat removed).
Add remaining ingredients to broth.
Cook on low-medium heat until vegetables are tender, 30 to 45 minutes.
Add salt to taste and usually 4 to 6 chicken bouillon cubes.

title: chocolate cheesecake brownies
directions: Heat oven to 325°F.
Grease a 9x13 baking pan.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In bowl, stir eggs, sugar, Karo syrup, chocolate chips, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Knife in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: sky high biscuits
directions: Combine first six ingredients. Cut in butter till crumbly. Combine egg and milk, stir into crumb mixture just until moistened. Knead 10-15 times on floured surface. Roll out one inch thick for 2 1/2 inch cutter, greased pan. Bake 450 degrees for 10-12 minutes. Makes one dozen. Can be used as a base for creamed turkey, chicken or sausage gravy.

title: navajo fried bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients together and mix in shortening. Gradually add the warm water.
Mix gently and knead until dough is soft to handle.
Cover and let dough rise about 30 minutes. Roll into small 2-inch balls (about the size of an egg). Flatten with hands and make a hole in the center (resembles a doughnut).
Drop into hot vegetable oil (3/4-inch deep). Turn when golden brown. Dust with powered sugar. Serve immediately.
Jam is also good with this bread.
Can also use recipe to make tacos. Roll enough dough to make a 1/4-inch thick taco shell about the size of a salad plate.
Fry one side folding over carefully to make a pocket. When golden brown remove then fill pocket with meat, cheese, lettuce, and sauce and roll.

title: health bar cookies
directions: Cook slowly to soft ball stage.
Pour over dry ingredients. Spoon into foil or (colored) cupcake papers.
Use your imagination to decorate each cookie.
Use small edible flowers, colorful after-dinner mints or a standing up almond or pecan.

title: fast-fix chocolate frosting
directions: Mix together 1/3 cup soft butter or regular margarine and 3 cups sifted confectioners sugar.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and enough milk to make mixture of spreading consistency (about 3 tablespoons).
Melt and cool 3 squares unsweetened chocolate; stir into frosting.

title: sugar-free popsicles
directions: Combine ingredients and freeze in trays with sticks.

title: cheesy new potatoes
directions: Cover potatoes with salted water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook about 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain potatoes and cool slightly.
Stir in butter and pepper; toss lightly. Spoon half of potato mixture into a lightly greased, 3 quart casserole.
Top with half each of bacon and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool.
Ice with vanilla icing and top with coconut.

title: orange juice creamsicles
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.
(You may want to add a little water to thin out slightly.) Makes delicious drink or freeze for popsicles.

title: alaska sheet cake
directions: Boil
margarine
and
water; add sugar, flour and salt. In small
bowl,
mix egg whites, buttermilk, soda and vanilla. Mix together
well.
Add
to first mixture.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chili pepper water
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in sealed jar and keep refrigerated.

title: yummy no cook letters or numbers
directions: Mix together and it's ready to use. Give each child (or mommy or daddy) a portion on a piece of waxed paper.
They can make letters or numbers and eat them.
Yummy!

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Melt oleo and pour over cracker crumbs.
Add 1 cup cold milk and Dream Whip (not too thick).
Pour sugar over cream cheese and make into a dish, reserving a few tablespoons for the top.
Put 1/2 of Dream Whip and cream cheese mixture over crumbs; the other half of cherries mixture.
Sprinkle other half of mixture over top.
Place in refrigerator.
Make the day before.

title: celery and water chestnut casserole
directions: Cook celery in a small amount of water until crisp about 8 minutes; drain.
Mix celery with water chestnuts, soup and pimentos.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Toss bread crumbs, almonds and butter together.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until lightly browned and hot.

title: fruit salad from nigeria
directions: Wash and peel mangoes.
Cut into bite size cubes.
Peel and slice bananas.
Cut tomato in half, remove seeds, and cut into cubes.
Combine mangoes, bananas, tomato and pineapple in a large bowl, toss (careful not to mash the fruit).

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the shrimp. Arrange shrimp on lettuce. Cover with sauce. Put tomatoes, sliced and quartered, on the side. Serves 4.

title: cocktail wieners with mustard sauce
directions: Mix first four ingredients and add cream and egg yolk.
Cook until mixtures thickens and add cider vinegar.
Cook until mixture coats spoon.
Add wieners.
Heat until cooked through.
Serve in chafing dish.

title: "a plus" broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli, garlic salt, sprinkled cheese and sauce. Continue layering; use sauce layer last.
Crumble crackers on top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes (check after 30 minutes) at 350°. May need to continue baking if deep layers until all is hot.

title: potatoes italiano
directions: Peel potatoes; dice into 1-inch cubes.
Melt 1/2 cup of butter, cool and then pour it into a plastic bag.
Add potatoes, crumbs and onion; shake until potatoes are coated.

title: applesauce puffs
directions: Combine Bisquick mix, sugar and cinnamon.
Add applesauce, milk, egg and oil.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Fill greased 2-inch muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in a 400° oven for 12 minutes or until done.
Cool slightly; remove.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter. Dip tops of muffins, then dip into sugar mixed with cinnamon. Yields 36 mini muffins.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and put in bread loaf pan. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour or until done.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots slightly.
When cooled, cover with other ingredients.
Let stand overnight.
Will keep 2 or 3 weeks or longer in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter, shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla together until creamy.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to creamy mixture; blend well.
Stir in coconut, nuts and oats. Roll into balls the size of walnuts and mash down on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: miracle coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and biscuit mix until smooth.
Add vanilla, margarine, milk and coconut.
Blend together and pour into 9-inch plate.
Heat oven to 350° and bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Pie makes its own crust.

title: ham wraparounds
directions: Cook fresh asparagus in 1-quart casserole dish in boiling salted water until tender, 9 to 10 minutes.
(Canned asparagus may be used.)
Melt butter in 1-quart casserole; stir in flour.
Add milk; cook until thick.
Stir every 30 seconds.
Beat egg yolks and stir into flour and milk mixture.
Add seasoning.
Wrap 3 stalks of asparagus in each slice of ham.
Lay bundles in glass utility dish and cover with sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and cook with microwave for 4 1/2 minutes.
Serve on toast. Recipe yields 4 servings.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine the sugar and cocoa; add the other ingredients (except pie shell).
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lemon sponge-cake pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Grate lemon rind; add to flour mixture.
Set aside.
Separate eggs; beat yolks.
To egg yolks, add lemon juice, milk and melted butter.
Add liquid mixture to dry mixture; mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into above.
Prepare favorite crust in 9-inch pan.
Pour in filling; bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: sweet hot mustard
directions: Mix dry mustard and vinegar until smooth.
Refrigerate overnight.
With electric beater, add eggs and sugar.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Stir to prevent scorching.
(Use beater for lumps.)

title: potato rolls(quick and easy)
directions: Mix in large mixing bowl:
mashed potatoes, sugar, salt and shortening.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk and add to other ingredients, then add flour and mix thoroughly (I use mixer with dough hook).
Let rise in bowl 10 minutes.
Turn out on floured board.
Roll out and cut like biscuits.
Put in greased pan.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake in preheated oven (400°) for 10 minutes until light brown.
Brush with butter.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut up eggs into small pieces.
Add mayonnaise, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix together well.
Spread on crackers, bread, etc.

title: vel-log
directions: Blend well and roll into a log shape.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter clusters
directions: Blend sugar and syrup.
When blended, bring to a boil.
Lower heat and mix in peanut butter and corn flakes.
Scoop in pan and press into pan.
Cut in squares.
Let harden.

title: indonesian chicken breasts
directions: Beat orange juice, peanut butter and curry powder in medium nonmetal bowl, using wire whisk. Add chicken, turning to coat with marinade. Cover and refrigerate, turning once, at least 1 hour but no longer than 24 hours.

title: moist apple cake
directions: Let apples and sugar stand for 45 minutes.
Stir frequently. Mix together ingredients and add to apple mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put in a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: clam casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour in pan surrounded by hot water.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter in dish.
Add wine, seasoned salt and garlic.
Add shrimp.
Place in oven on broil for 6 minutes, then turn over and cook for another 5 to 6 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: island pineapple salad
directions: Combine the oranges, pineapple, cottage cheese, dry gelatin and pecans.
Mix well.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and put into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Cool.

title: pot roast
directions: Place piece of foil, 30 x 18-inches, in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place beef in pan.
Mix mushroom soup and onion soup mix.
Spread over beef.
Add vegetables.
Sprinkle with water. Fold foil over and seal.
Cook in a 300° oven 4 hours.
Skim fat from gravy. Serve gravy with beef. Serves 8.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream the sugar, eggs and salt.
Add remaining ingredients to creamed mixture.
Bake in layers at 350°.
When springs from touch, cake is done.

title: pritikin's chicken in a skillet
directions: Cook 1/2 cup brown rice and set aside.
Cover the bottom of a skillet with orange juice. Add minced onion, tarragon and pepper. Cut up chicken breast in small pieces. Cook until white on both sides; turn down if boils.
Add sliced banana. Cover and simmer. Put brown rice on plate.
Cover with contents from the skillet. Serves 1 person.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture gradually, mixing well.
Add nuts.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut in bars.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, garlic and salt; drain and add remaining ingredients.
Heat in crock-pot.
Dip chips, crackers, bread, etc.

title: enchilada casserole #2
directions: Brown meat and
add
taco seasoning.
Cook according to directions on package.
Mix
soups, Ro-Tel and milk. In an 8 x 10-inch baking
dish,
layer alternately tortilla pieces, meat and soup.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add marshmallow cream.
When well blended, add Cook Whip.
Serve with apples, bananas, grapes, strawberries, etc.

title: corned beef-chili wraps
directions: Mix together; put on hamburger buns.
Wrap in foil and heat at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash beans.
Add 1 1/2 quarts water.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Transfer to crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 300° for 5 to 6 hours.
Check every 2 hours and add more liquid when needed.

title: salad supreme
directions: Spread frozen peas on paper towel.
Thaw and dry.
Place first five ingredients in large container.
Combine rest and spread over top of salad.
Refrigerate overnight, covered with damp cloth, just before serving.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter on low heat. Add remaining ingredients and blend. Pour into 8-inch pie pan that has been floured and lined.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool slightly. Remove paper lining. Serve with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.
Can freeze.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Flatten hamburger meat in baking pan all around.
Spread the vegetables on top of meat.
Put mushroom soup on vegetables; spread out the Tater Tots.
Cook at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: crescent barbecue bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large frying pan, brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce; simmer.
To prepare crust, separate crescent dough into 2 large rectangles. Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press over and up 1 inch on sides to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Spread hot meat mixture over dough and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Cut pocket in each side of chicken breast.
Fold ham around cheese and stuff in chicken pocket.
Melt oleo in pie plate.
Mix crumbs, salt and pepper and paprika on second pie plate.
Roll chicken in oleo then in crumbs.
Bake in buttered dish at 400° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: winter vegetable soup
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons of butter until soft, but not brown.
Add flour and stir over moderate heat for 2 minutes. Gradually add chicken broth, whisking until smooth.
Add potatoes and seasoning and simmer, uncovered, until potatoes are almost tender.

title: fast and easy cottage cheese loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased casserole or loaf pan.
Serve with gravy or plain.
May be used sliced cold for sandwiches.
Serves 6.

title: taco meat loaf
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Mix in taco shells and cheese.
Shape into loaf in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cooked through.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut off wing tips and wrap and freeze for stock/broth.
Cut chicken wings into two pieces, separating them at the joint.
Put the 36 parts in each of 2 large shallow roasting pans.
Combine the soy sauce and the sugars and pour the mixture over the chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from the oven and turn each piece.
Return pans to the oven for 30 minutes. Turn the wings again and cook for about 20 minutes longer or until mahogany colored and very tender.
Transfer wings to a large, warm platter and garnish with a bouquet of parsley.

title: christmas goodies
directions: Crush pecans or other nuts and pretzels.
Melt caramels with water.
Add all together; mix well.
Make into small balls.

title: nacho dip
directions: Melt cheese.
Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Add to cheese.
Add salsa.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together oleo, sugar, peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Pat together.
Pat mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Have your mom melt the chocolate chips for you in a pan or the microwave and pour those melted chips over the mixture.
Let it cool and cut into bars.
Keep it in the fridge.

title: german chocolate bars
directions: Combine all ingredients with a mixer.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour in a greased and floured 12 x 15-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crush crackers.
Add melted oleo and sugar.
Mix and save 1/2 cup.
Pat the rest in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix instant pudding and milk.
Add softened ice cream.
Mix and pour on crumbs.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup crumbs.

title: tex-mexican chops
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Add salsa and chillies.
Cook over low heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add all other ingredients. Stir and bake in covered casserole for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Can microwave for 18 minutes instead.
Serves 4.

title: cheesy mostaccioli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook mostaccioli according to directions; drain. Cook ground beef until almost done. Add onions and green pepper; finish cooking until no pink remains. Stir in seasonings, spaghetti sauce and soup. Mix well. Combine mostaccioli, meat sauce and 1 1/2 cups of the Mozzarella cheese. Place in a 9 x 13 baking dish and cover. Bake 35 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: cole slaw(no mayonnaise)
directions: Shred cabbage.
Finely chop pepper, pimento and onions.
Boil together 1 minute: salad oil, vinegar, sugar, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Keeps up to two weeks.
Gets better daily.
Can substitute fresh red sweet pepper for pimiento.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain.
Start layering ingredients in casserole dish.
Start with shredded cabbage, then beef, salt, onion, then Hunt's special sauce.
Keep layering until you reach top of dish.
Be sure Hunt's special sauce is on top.
Pour water in.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients together; chill.

title: broccoli, cheese and rice
directions: Mix in pan the soups, milk and Cheez Whiz.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Add broccoli, rice and onion.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Dump all in a bowl; mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 35 to 40 minutes; leave in pan.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan or angel food pan.
Place frozen rolls in pan.
Mix brown sugar and pudding mix and sprinkle over rolls.
Mix granulated sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over pudding layer.
Spread pecans over this and pour melted butter over all. Let set, uncovered, overnight on countertop.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set in pan 15 minutes and then slice or pull apart to serve.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Rub butter in bottom of pan.
Put rice, chicken, onions, celery and green peppers in pan.
Add soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all together thoroughly.
Put in a greased 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese log
directions: Work all together.
Makes 2 rolls.
Sprinkle wax paper with paprika.
Roll up and store in refrigerator.

title: tea brandy slush
directions: Mix all ingredients in ice cream bucket or large container. Store in freezer for 24 hours before serving.
Scoop out about 3/4 serving per glass, filling the remainder of the glass with white soda.
Garnish with a stem cherry.

title: beets in orange sauce
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch and mix well.
Add orange juice and butter.
Cook in top of double boiler 5 minutes or until thick.
Pour over heated drained beets.

title: cheater salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and sprinkle in jello. (Any flavor can be used depending on color desired.) Mix well.

title: brisket
directions: Sprinkle celery, garlic, and onion salts on brisket.
Rub on liquid smoke.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, pour off juice.
Salt and pepper to taste and sprinkle with worcestershire sauce.
Bake covered for 3 hours at 275°.
Drain juice, cover with barbecue sauce and bake an additional hour at 250°.
Slice and serve.

title: sweet and sour stew
directions: In a large pan, brown meat.
Add onion and garlic.
Add water and cover.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until tender.

title: perfect sunday dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and add sugar. Separately beat eggs and 1 cup warm water. Then add oil and salt. Add this to the yeast mixture and gradually add the flour. This will be sticky. That's okay. Let stand overnight with waxed paper or paper towel covering it. Use a large bowl as it will grow. Before Sunday School, pat out the dough and cut with a biscuit cutter. Place cutouts on a greased cookie sheet and let stand until after church. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Place bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot salad
directions: Boil together for 5 minutes, all ingredients except carrots. Pour over carrots.
Green peppers may be added for extra color and flavor.
Can be served hot or cold and keeps well in refrigerator for several days.
Best if made day ahead.

title: luscious pineapple cream pie
directions: Combine milk, pineapple, Cool Whip and pecans.
Add lemon juice and mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shells and chill until set.
Garnish each slice with a cherry.

title: 3 can hot dip
directions: Layer 1:
1 can bean
dip and 1 can refried beans.
Mix and spread into large round platter.

title: marble cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, cocoa, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla, mix well. Pour half the batter evenly over crust.
Stir melted chocolate into remaining batter; spoon over vanilla batter.
With table knife gently swirl through batter to marble.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and chill.
Cut into bars.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter. Pour into baking dish, sprayed with Pam. Put butter on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix flour, melted margarine and nuts.
Spread in bottom of dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: pecan goodies
directions: Break crackers into 1/4 of each cracker and place on a cookie sheet with sides.
Sprinkle each cracker with broken pecan pieces. Set aside.
Mix oleo, butter and sugar in a boiler. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
After mix boils, let boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Spoon butter mixture over the crackers and pecans. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Place each little cracker on waxed paper and let cool. Do not let crackers touch.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Bring all ingredients to boiling in a large saucepan.
Simmer covered for 30 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve hot.
Garnish with slices of unpared red apples.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: quick chipped beef dip
directions: Blend the dip and cream cheese well until smooth.
Stir in chipped beef.

title: semi-sweet chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave chocolate and margarine in a large microwavable bowl on High for 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Stir sugar into melted chocolate mixture.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix until well blended.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Spread into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out with fudgy crumbs.
Do not overbake!
Cool in pan; cut into squares.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onion in a large skillet over medium-high heat; pour off fat.
Add all other ingredients, except buns, mixing well.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Place pie crust in deep pie pan and add mixture.
Cover with Cheddar cheese slices.
Place another pie crust on top.
Seal and make slits in top crust.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400° and for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: cream cheese olive sandwich
directions: Cook bacon, reserving drippings.
Crumble bacon.
Beat cream cheese and Miracle Whip to spreading consistency.
Stir in olives and crumbled bacon.
Add spices and refrigerate.
Can be used as open face sandwiches for a party.
It is very colorful for any occasion.

title: andouille & potato soup
directions: In a large pot, over medium heat, add the olive oil.
When the oil is hot, add the onions and saute for 2 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add the sausage and continue to saute to 2 minutes.
Stir in the garlic and herbs.
Add the potatoes and stock.
Bring the liquid to a boil and reduce to a simmer, simmering for 30 minutes.
Add chopped parsley and season with salt and pepper.

title: pineapple-orange sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients and churn until frozen.

title: cherry surprise cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover the bottom of dish with the marshmallows.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Mix the cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer until smooth.
Place the mixture on top of vanilla wafer in baking cups.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°; top with pie filling. Yields approximately 3 dozen.

title: mckenzie goulash
directions: Saute onions in oil until tender.
Add caraway seed, marjoram, salt and paprika moistened with vinegar.
Mix with onions.
Pour in wine.
Cover tightly and simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, or until meat is tender.
If necessary, add water sparingly during cooking. Serve with noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato pie(this is the recipe for 2 pies.)
directions: Bake potatoes at 350° until done, if they were bought whole. Use potato masher to mash the potatoes.
(This is to free the potatoes from strings and etc., remove the large strings.)
Melt the margarine, mix in the potato and canned milk.
Beat eggs and add to the mixture.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Split the batter into 1/2.
Add each separate spice into each different batter and fill the pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: sour cream 'n' dill chicken
directions: Place chicken in a single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Combine soup, soup mix, sour cream, lemon juice, dill and mushrooms; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serve over egg noodles if desired.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain and mix all ingredients well with pudding.
Let set in refrigerator 30 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Melt and blend sugar, vegetable oil and chocolate.
Add in order:
eggs (one at a time), vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill mixture 3 hours/overnight.
Roll balls into powdered sugar.
Place 2-inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven. Cool, eat and enjoy.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs; cream bananas until fluffy and add.
Add sugar mixture alternating with dry ingredients.
Add chopped nuts and pour into greased loaf pan; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine, mix with sugar.
Add flour and milk.
Put in dish and place peaches on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a large 9-inch pie plate (makes its own crust).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla together.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: In mixing bowl mix, cream cheese and sugar, beat with electric mixer on high until blended.
Gently stir in cool whip.

title: hamburger hash
directions: Fry everything together. Serve.

title: tomato jelly
directions: Peel tomatoes.
Mash 3 cups. Follow Sure-Jel recipe for making jelly.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Pour beans into a greased casserole.
Combine sugar, mustard and catsup.
Stir mixture into beans.
Slightly bake bacon in oven or microwave to remove some of grease.
Cut bacon in pieces and place over beans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: apple bar dessert
directions: Mix flour, oleo and brown sugar and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Prepare instant pudding and pour over hot bars.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: marissa's favorite cabbage soup
directions: Brown turkey or beef in large pot.
Add all ingredients except parsley; when adding whole tomatoes, break them up with a big spoon.
Do not puree.
Bring to a boil; reduce to a simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Serve with fresh bread.

title: spinach scalloped franks
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour; add milk. Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese, stirring until melted.
Arrange half the potatoes evenly in a baking dish.
Top with half of franks and half of spinach and sauce.
Repeat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and bake uncovered until cheese melts. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix thoroughly and form into a ball.
Serve with wheat stone crackers.

title: sour cream blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg, sugar, sour cream and oil until blended.
Combine dry ingredients (flour, soda and salt).
Add to other ingredients and beat until blended. Stir in blueberries and scrape sides with spatula combining all ingredients.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin pans or muffin cups. Fill 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in small amount of Crisco.
Add tomatoes and cook to a thick paste.
In a boiler mix flour with enough milk to make a paste.
Add mushroom soup and cheese and cook until thick.
Add English peas.
Add the two mixtures together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake until crumbs are browned.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Crust Layer:
Blend together flour and oleo.
Add chopped pecans.
Put mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Cover strawberries with water and bring almost to a boil. (Scald for about 2 minutes.)
Drain berries and return to pan. Add 4 cups sugar; boil 3 or 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
When mixture stops bubbling, add 2 more cups sugar.
Boil 7 to 10 minutes.
Spread on tray or in shallow pan.
Cool overnight.
Put in jars.

title: kolacky
directions: Blend oleo, flour and baking powder as for pie dough; add sour cream and milk.
Work with hands until smooth.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll and cut into squares, add filling and fold 2 opposite corners to meet each other.
Brush with egg white.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: venison chili
directions: Soak beans.
Place in roaster with enough water to cover plus 1 inch over.
Cook until almost tender, about 2 hours. Meanwhile, brown meat and onion in oil.
Add this and all other ingredients to beans and return to oven for 1 hour.

title: pralines
directions: Caramelize 1
cup sugar in a frying pan, then pour into large pot
with
remaining
cups of sugar, butter and milk. Cook until
mixture
forms
a soft ball in water.
Remove from heat and add
vanilla and chopped pecans.
Beat until mixture looks like fudge.
Pour out on buttered surface and cool.
Cut into desired size.

title: brown sugar pecans delights
directions: Bring margarine and brown sugar to a boil.
Boil a few minutes.
Add pecans.
Place graham crackers on a cookie sheet covered with aluminum foil sprayed with Pam.
Pour pecan mixture over graham crackers. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: miss inez's million dollar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and flavorings.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown beef; cut up cheese and add tomatoes. Turn down to simmer, stirring a few times until cheese is melted. Serve with large Fritos for dipping.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Put hot dogs into a crock-pot and add grape jelly and chili sauce.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours until hot.

title: taco ring
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine cooked meat, taco seasoning, cheese and water in 2-quart batter bowl. Arrange crescent triangles in a circle on 15-inch baking stone with bases overlapping in center and points to the outside. There should be a 5-inch diameter circle in center. Scoop meat mixture over crescent rolls with medium stainless steel scoop. Fold points of triangles over filling and tuck under base at center. Filling will not be completely covered. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. V-cut green pepper using V-shaped cutter. Shred lettuce and cube tomato with 5-inch utility knife. Chop onion with food chopper. Slice olives using egg slicer. Place V-cut pepper in center of ring; fill with salsa. Mound lettuce, onion, tomato and olives around pepper. Garnish with sour cream. Cut with pizza cutter; serve with mini-serving spatula. Yield: 8 servings or 20 sample servings.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Slice potatoes and add onion and salt. Add vinegar and sugar to bacon and fat in skillet and bring to a boil. Pour over potatoes and mix. Serve at once. Serves 6.

title: 7 layer mexican dip
directions: Mix first three ingredients and press in the bottom of an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix taco sauce or salsa with sour cream and pour over avocado mixture, then layer with cheese, peppers, tomatoes and onions.
Just dip your favorite chips in.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease jellyroll pan, cookie sheet or bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Pat dough in pan and pinch sides.
Cook and stir ground beef, onion, bouillon and garlic until beef is brown and bouillon is dissolved.
Mix tomato sauce and oregano.
Spread evenly over dough.
Spoon beef mixture evenly over sauce.
Top with mushrooms, green pepper and cheese.
Bake until crust is golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook 1st 7 ingredients in large kettle until tender.
Then add soup and milk.
When heated, add Velveeta.
Put on low heat until cheese is melted, then serve.

title: apricot congealed salad
directions: Boil sugar and water in microwave 5 to 6 minutes.
Add apricot Jell-O.
Stir, then add baby food.
Mix well and set aside to cool.
Whip sweetened condensed milk and cream cheese.
Add crushed pineapple and nuts with cooled Jell-O and apricot baby food mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish which has been rubbed with mayonnaise.
Chill until set.

title: pizza dip
directions: Simmer and serve hot.
Add cheese last.
Dip with chips.

title: fresh apple salad(sweet and sour)
directions: Mix first three ingredients together in medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add vinegar last because it might curdle.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Cool.
Pour over 4 cups fresh cut apples.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients well and put in baking
dish, greased with margarine.

title: bean salad
directions: Slice
pepper and onion in rings.
Mix all ingredients. Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Makes 20 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in large casserole.
Put French fries, peas and beef in layers until it is used up.
Mix soup, water and parsley; pour over top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef, onion and rosemary.
Break up into small pieces.
Spoon off fat.
Add 1/2 cup gravy and pepper. Mix well.
Spread meat and vegetables.
Use a quart casserole or deep dish pie pan.
Cover with potatoes to edge to seal.
Heat oven at 375°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until potatoes are golden.
Serve with remaining gravy on side.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss everything together.
Add crushed chips just before serving.

title: beans and greens
directions: Wash the escarole until water is clear.
Break into small pieces. Add to boiling water. Cook until soft. Drain.
If using white kidney beans, soak overnight, drain and add fresh water. Cook 1 1/2 hours and drain.
In a Dutch oven pan, saute the garlic cloves in the olive oil.
Add beans and greens.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add vegetable broth as desired (if you feel it needs more liquid).
Cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes on low heat.

title: basic sweet roll dough
directions: Mix first three ingredients together. Put yeast in and stir until dissolved.
Stir in eggs, shortening and flour in two parts. Knead dough gently.
Should be almost sticky.
Put in greased bowl and let rise until double.
Shape into whatever shapes you wish.
Sticky buns, doughnuts, coffee cake or just plain pan rolls.
Bake at 425° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: aunt callie's pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Wash onions and cut into 1/8-inch slices.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Let set at room temperature 2 hours, then place in glass or plastic containers and refrigerate until used.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes (until nicely browned).

title: super nacho
directions: Brown beef, onion, seasoned salt and cumin; drain.
Combine beans, taco seasoning and cheese for bean mixture.
Spread bean mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with meat and onion mixture. Sprinkle with green chiles.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Pour taco sauce over top.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Garnish with sour cream, tomatoes, green onions, black olives, etc. Eat with tortilla chips.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat in.
Sift flour and baking powder together in separate bowl and set aside.
Start with the flour mixture, adding one cup at a time to the creamed mixture.
Alternate with 1/3 cup milk until all flour and milk has been blended together.
Add flavorings to batter.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
Cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli as directed on package.
In casserole dish, melt butter.
Add diced onion, rice, broccoli, soup, Cheez Whiz and milk.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baxter's chili
directions: Brown beef, onions, and bell peppers, drain. Add other ingredients and simmer for 2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend well.
Add a variety of vegetables, cut bite size.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in flour to make a smooth paste.
Add creamer very slowly; stir until smooth. Add corn, eggs and pepper.
Set casserole in a pan filled with hot water 1 inch deep.
Bake at 350° until firm, 45 to 50 minutes. Serves 4.

title: pork chops braised with prunes
directions: Buy pork chops.
Slowly brown chops on both sides in a preheated skillet for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add sliced onions, prunes, water, brown sugar, cider vinegar and red hot sauce.
Cover and cook over low heat about 1 hour or until tender.
Serve on warm platter.

title: taco mac salad
directions: Cook noodles as directed; drain and rinse with cold water. Brown meat; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning; mix well.
Cool.
In large bowl, mix noodles, green pepper, onion, cheese, tomatoes and lettuce seasoning.
Chill.
Stir meat in just before serving. Crumble taco chips and mix with French dressing just before serving.

title: carrot cake and icing
directions: Beat eggs and oil.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture and beat.
Add carrots and nuts to mix. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan (greased) or 3 (9-inch) greased layer pans.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° if using layer pans, or 35 to 40 minutes if using 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Let cheese get to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients and let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken cut up into pieces.
Mix sour cream, soup, chilies and chicken; spread over chips.
Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: lazy day casserole
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place ingredients in casserole in layers.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Pour 1/2 cup French fried onions.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven until bubbly, about 25 minutes.
Remove cover and pour 1/2 cup onions over top. Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: smoothie
directions: You will need a blender.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Remove caps. Crush berries one layer at a time. Combine fruit and lemon juice. Add sugar. Mix thoroughly and let stand 10 minutes. Combine water and pectin in a small saucepan. Boil hard 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add cooked pectin to fruit mixture and stir for 3 minutes. Ladle jam into jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace. Screw on lids and let jam
stand until set, but no longer than 24 hours. Store in freezer for up to 1 year.

title: bakery cake icing
directions: Cream half of the sugar with shortening.
Add egg whites, mixing well.
Add sugar and flavoring.
Beat until smooth.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: mac and cheese casserole with zucchini
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, prepare macaroni and cheese, but use 1 1/4 cups milk and 4 tablespoons butter or margarine (1/2 stick).
Slice zucchini into 1/4-inch slices.
In skillet over medium high heat in 2 tablespoons hot margarine, cook zucchini in batches until golden brown.
Remove to plate as they brown.
Into 13 x 9-inch baking dish, spoon 1/2 macaroni and cheese and top with 1/2 zucchini.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350° until cheese melts and is heated through. Yields 8 servings.

title: wellesley fudge cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs. Add dry ingredients alternating with sour milk. Blend in cocoa mixture. Grease and flour two 8-inch cake pans. Divide cake mix in each pan. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix all and form into ball. Refrigerate 1 hour and serve with crackers.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown meat lightly.
Add onions and green pepper; saute until onions are clear (not browned).
Drain.
Add tomatoes, salt and chili powder.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix cornbread mix according to directions on the box.
Pour over top of meat mixture and bake until cornbread is done, 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine butter, syrup, sugar and salt in an 8 cup glass measuring cup or bowl.
Bring to a boil in microwave and then cook 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir in baking soda.
Put corn in large brown grocery bag that has been sprayed with Pam.
Pour syrup over corn and stir lightly to combine.
Put the bag in the microwave; cook 2 1/2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Remove from microwave and spread on a cookie sheet to cool.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour or if frozen, bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: double cheese delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package. Drain. In large skillet, cook and stir meat, onions and celery until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and salt.
Heat to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream and noodles.
Pour into greased 1-1/2 qt casserole dish. Cover.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: lemony-stuffed fish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 1 quart saucepan melt 1/3 cup butter over medium heat.
Add celery and onion.
Saute until tender. Stir in stuffing mix, parsley, lemon juice and peel, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Cut each fillet to make 8 (3 x 4-inch) pieces.
Place 4 halves in ungreased baking dish.
Top each with 1/4 cup stuffing mixture, then remaining fillet halves.
Melt 1/3 cup butter.
Stir in dill weed.
Pour dill-butter over fillets. Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Watch closely.

title: party wieners
directions: Cut meat in bite-size pieces.
Mix mustard and jelly in a 1-quart saucepan.
Add meat.
Cover and cook at low heat for 10 minutes.
Serve on toothpicks with crackers.
Makes 3/4 cup sauce.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with dough.
Mix until well blended all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°. Reduce heat to 350° and bake about 45 minutes longer, until an inserted knife comes out clean.
I make a strip of aluminum foil to cover the edge of pie crust.
It keeps it from getting too brown. Beat a half pint of whipping cream with 1/4 cup of sugar in a glass bowl until stiff for topping.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.	Melt butter in 9 x 13 baking dish and mix all ingredients (including butter).
Pour into baking dish.
Cook at 350° in oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: one dish meal
directions: Layer in casserole dish and top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: sunday night dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning according to package directions.
Spread meat in the bottom of a 9-inch microwave-safe serving dish.
Spread sour cream on top of ground beef.
Pour salsa on top of sour cream.
Sprinkle cheddar cheese on top of salsa.
Garnish with black olives, if desired. Microwave 30 to 40 seconds or long enough to melt cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: baked mustard chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix milk and mustard in small bowl. In separate bowl, combine bread crumbs and spices.
Coat chicken pieces with milk mixture, then roll chicken in bread crumbs. Place chicken pieces in shallow baking pan.
Do not overlap pieces.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.
Yields 4 servings.

title: garlic biscuits
directions: First, place the 10 biscuits in a deep dish (pie).
Pour the melted butter over the biscuits; completely saturate the individual biscuits by rotating them.
Next, sprinkle the desired amount of garlic salt, Parmesan cheese and parsley over the biscuits.

title: shrimp cocktail dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.
Serve with potato chips or crackers.

title: peaches and cream bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, 2 eggs, melted margarine and frosting mix.
Stir by hand until cake mix is moistened, press into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.

Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, remove from oven and top with drained peaches. In a small mixing bowl, combine sour cream with one egg, pour evenly over peaches and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple pecan muffins
directions: Combine milk and bran in large bowl.
Let set 5 minutes.
Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add egg, oil and dry ingredients to milk and bran.
Mix only until all ingredients are moist, should be lumpy.
Stir in pecans and pineapple.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields fourteen muffins.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and butter until fluffy.
Add sugar and flavorings.
Mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat 2 minutes.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours or until done when tested.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together butter, sugar and flour.
Pat half of dough into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine rest of ingredients and layer over crust.
Sprinkle reserved flour mixture over apple filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pizza potato topping
directions: In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, pepperoni, cheeses and pizza sauce.
Serve over baked potatoes.
Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: string beans
directions: Wash, remove strings and snap or cut into 1-inch pieces.
Cook in boiling, salted water.
Season with butter or side bacon.

title: mango cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: In a pot on the stove top, add enough water to cover potatoes, then cook until potatoes are soft or about 50 minutes. Remove potatoes from water and let cool.

title: light ginger cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, margarine and vinegar.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
(If dough is too dry, work in milk or cream, 1 teaspoon at a time.)
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutters; place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake until light brown, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly; carefully remove from cookie sheet.
Decorate with frosting.

title: basic white sauce
directions: Combine milk, flour and Butter Buds in a small saucepan. Heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Season with pepper and lite salt. Use when you need a cream sauce as in macaroni and cheese or creamed chicken or tuna.
Yields 2 cups, 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in bottom of greased pan. Mix tother flour, sugar, milk and butter and pour over fruit. Bake until golden brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all above ingredients together.
Add small amount of water if dry.
Form into walnut size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 325 degree oven
20 to 25 minutes.
You may have to turn once.

title: oatmeal fudge cookies
directions: Cut open a paper bag and place on table with wax paper laid on top.
Cook sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes, start timing when mixture has reached a full rolling boil (this is important).
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla, oats and nuts.
Pour on wax paper; cool completely.
Cut.

title: pasta and beans
directions: Cook ditalini according to package directions.
Fry bacon and set aside.
Add chopped onions to bacon grease and brown.
Add the tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add the beans and bacon.
Simmer again for 20 minutes.
Pour this over the cooked ditalini.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: bean bake
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add tomatoes and simmer 15 minutes. Add beans, salt, pepper and chili seasoning.
Simmer 15 minutes. Sprinkle chips in flat baking dish.
Pour meat mixture over and add grated cheese.
Bake at 350° or long enough to melt cheese. Serves 8.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into bite-size balls. You may freeze them at this point.
(If frozen, take them out 1/2 hour before baking.)
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients together in shallow bowl.
Add wings and marinate overnight.
Then bake in hot oven, 400°, until crisp and richly glazed.
(May also be used as an appetizer.)

title: hot rolls
directions: Stir yeast, sugar, salt and warm water in a bowl.
Cool scalded milk to lukewarm and add to mixture.
Add 1 cup of flour, 1 beaten egg and the melted shortening.
Beat together.
Add 2 cups of flour and beat.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and make into rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake in hot oven at about 375°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain macaroni.
Stir in grated cheese until well blended.
Put in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake until cheese on top is melted.

title: creamy dutch apple
directions: In 1 1/2-quart shallow dish (10 x 6), combine butter and graham cracker crumbs. Press in bottom of dish. Mix together Eagle Brand, sour cream and lemon. Spread evenly over crumbs. Spread pie filling evenly over creamy layer. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until set. Cool slightly. Mix nuts and cinnamon together. Sprinkle over top.

title: funnel cake
directions: *Batter needs to be thin.
Add milk until desired consistency.

title: yogurt-dill sauce
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine yogurt, dill weed, pepper and garlic powder.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with fish, seafood or lamb.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: chocoholic brownies
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine and stir in Choco-Bake. In mixer bowl, beat eggs and vanilla.
