Add sugar.
Blend in the chocolate mixture.
Add flour and salt.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 24 large squares (9 x 13-inch)

title: jai alai caramel custard
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Boil marshmallows and 7-Up until marshmallows are melted. Add jello. Stir until dissolved. Pour over cream cheese. Blend together. Add pineapple. Chill until partially set up. Mix Cool Whip and mayo into it. Chill and serve. Better if sets overnight.

title: italian spinach(even if you hate spinach)
directions: Add eggs and Parmesan cheese to cooked spinach.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix all together and crumble on top 1/2 cup soft bread crumbs and 1 tablespoon melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: celebration sandwiches
directions: Cut turkey or ham into small pieces and finely grind in a food processor or food grinder. Transfer to a mixing bowl. Add chives, mayonnaise or salad dressing, sour cream, almonds or pecans and celery to ground turkey. Stir until mixture is well combined and of spreading consistency. Cover and store in the refrigerator for up to 2 days. Spread the turkey mixture on bread or crackers. Garnish as desired. Makes about 2 1/2 cups filling, enough for 48 small, open-faced sandwiches.

title: new england clam chowder soup(microwave)
directions: Place bacon in 2-quart casserole; microwave at High 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove bacon, reserve drippings and drain bacon on paper towel.
Stir potatoes and onions into bacon drippings.
Cover; microwave on High 7 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Drain clams, reserving juice. Blend clam juice and mixture into potato mixture; microwave on High for 8 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Stir in clams and crumble bacon into mixture.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix; do not add all the water called for on cans of lemon juice, because you will want to add some ice.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover; refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening together.
Add sugar and eggs. Combine other ingredients.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: blueberry meringues
directions: In an electric mixer bowl, combine egg whites and cream of tartar.
Beat at high seed until egg whites are foamy. Gradually add sugar and continue beating until egg whites are very stiff and glossy, but not dry.
Fold in blueberries.
Line baking sheets with brown paper.
Drop meringue by spoonfuls onto paper about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 275° for 40 minutes or until firm but not browned.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: gertie's sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine the ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Then prepare topping and pour over potato mixture.
Place in 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together with an electric mixer.
Make sure they are thoroughly mixed.
Cover and chill 1/2 hour.
Divide into 2 or 4 sections, depending on size ball you want.
Roll balls in nuts and garnish.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix all ingredients together (cinnamon, sugar, flour, butter and water).
It will be crumbly.
Lay apples in baking dish. Add mixture to top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes enough to handle.
Save out 1/2 stick of margarine.
Mix all ingredients, except corn flakes.
Put into 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish or pan.
Melt 1/2 stick of margarine; mix with corn flakes and put on top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: vicki's crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients, cover and chill.
Best if made night before serving.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine shortening, sugars, beaten eggs and flavoring; blend well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, rolled oats, nuts and coconut. This is a stiff batter.
Roll 1 teaspoon dough about the size of a walnut; place on oiled cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Press slightly with bottom of a glass.
May be trimmed with gumdrops or colored sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350° until slightly browned.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil salted and peppered chicken.
Tear chicken apart in small pieces.
Set aside.
In chicken broth, cook spaghetti.
Saute chopped onion in butter.
Mix spaghetti, onion, drained English peas, tomatoes, soup and chicken.
Sprinkle Velveeta into mixture and mix together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot throughout.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling for 5 minutes over medium heat, or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in cocoa, vanilla, marshmallow cream and nuts; mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch square or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: sausage loaf
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly and slice.
This is great with scrambled eggs for brunch. This freezes well.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in large skillet.
Drain. Meanwhile, boil sliced potatoes until tender.
Add the soups to the ground beef.
Mix well.
Drain potatoes and put in the casserole dish.
Top with ground beef mixture.
Cut up toast into squares and spread over ground beef.
Cook at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first five ingredients, then add next three ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in three 9-inch pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes before removing.
After removing from pans, cool completely and spread frosting between layers, top and sides.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans on top.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Top with grated Hershey bar.
Chill.

title: frozen cheese cake
directions: Line bottom of oblong pan with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Cream well the cream cheese; add sugar and beat well.
Add egg yolks. Stir in pineapple and vanilla.
Blend in heavy whipped cream and stiffly beaten egg whites.
Sprinkle wafer crumbs on top for decoration.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Fry or saute broccoli, butter and onion.
Add cheese, soup, milk and salt.
Add rice. Put in baking dish and bake until bubbly or about 30 minutes.
Top with bread crumbs or crumbled Ritz crackers before baking.
Bake at 350°.

title: creamy mushroom-potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until tender; drain and mash (DO NOT ADD BUTTER OR MILK). In a skillet, saute onion and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter for 3 to 4 minutes or until just tender. Stir in potatoes along with sour cream, salt and pepper. Spoon into greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese; dot with remaining butter. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through and golden brown.

title: chocolate nut clusters
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, place chocolate chips and shortening.
Microwave at High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon heaping teaspoonfuls into 1-inch paper candy cups or small muffin cups, filling each cup about half full.
Refrigerate until firm.
Peel off paper cup if desired.
Makes about 14 to 16 pieces of candy.

title: bixby salad
directions: After jello congeals, whip until foamy.
Add remaining ingredients to jello.
Return to refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole]
directions: Boil chicken.
Let cool and pull from bone.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Put a layer of chicken, a layer of soup mixture and a layer of crackers.
Do this twice.
Melt margarine and pour over the top.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly with moist hands.
Shape into loaf and place in a shallow dish.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli, chopped onion and butter in small saucepan.
Put in just enough water to cover broccoli.
Cook until water is about gone.
Add soups, milk, salt, rice and pepper to taste.
Mix well. Pour mixture into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: turkey roll-ups
directions: Place 1 piece Swiss cheese on each cutlet.
Roll up; secure with toothpicks and place seam side down in baking dish.
Combine butter and seasonings.
Pour over rolls.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain and add rice and beans.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Place in casserole dish and grate cheese over top.
Cook at 300° for 15 minutes or so.

title: party potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes and cheese.
Stir in potatoes and cheese.
Spread in ungreased baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Sprinkle with cheese (if desired).
Cover and cook in 350° oven 1 hour.
Uncover and cook about 30 minutes.

title: german pancake
directions: Beat the flour and eggs until smooth.
Then add milk, butter and salt. Blend well and pour into a 9 or 10-inch well-greased ovenproof skillet or dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°.
Serve with butter and/or powdered sugar.

title: wilted cabbage salad
directions: Layer cabbage and onion in bowl.
Pour 2/3 cup sugar over and do not mix.
Combine oil, vinegar, salt, mustard, celery seed and 1 teaspoon sugar in saucepan.
Let come to a boil.
Pour hot dressing over cabbage, onions and sugar; do not mix.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 3 hours or overnight.
Mix before serving.

title: easy chocolate frosting
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa and milk to boil.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix until smooth and frost cake.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Melt the margarine in skillet. Saute in the margarine the onions and the celery and leaves. Add the salt, pepper, sage, thyme and poultry seasoning.

title: mother's peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter, add milk, heat, then add sugar and cook until bubbly, 12 to 15 minutes. Set off heat, add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
To test-drop into cold water to get "soft ball stage".
Place in pyrex square pan.
Let it cool, become firm and enjoy.

title: irene's lemon pie
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1 1/2 cups water and 1/2 teaspoon salt in saucepan and heat to boiling.
Mix cornstarch and 1/3 cup water in small bowl to make a smooth paste.
Gradually add this to the boiling mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick and clear.
Stir constantly!!
Remove from heat.
Combine egg yolks and lemon juice; stir into thickened mixture.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until the mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and lemon peel.
Cover and let cool until lukewarm.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Let chill.
Beat cream cheese, vanilla and 7-Up.
Beat all together until creamy, then add to jello mixture with small can of crushed pineapple and nuts.
Chill.

title: date-nut carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400.
Line 12 muffin tins with muffin paper or spray with non-stick spray.
In a medium bow, stir muffin mix, bran, milk, and eggs.
Fold in carrots and dates.
(Batter should be lumpy.)
Place in muffin tins.
Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add the eggs, one at a time. Add the sifted dry ingredients alternately with the milk.
Fold in the blueberries.
Place in greased muffin tins and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
The batter will keep in the refrigerator in a covered bowl for 2 or 3 weeks and can be baked as needed.

title: caesar salad dressing from mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl until evenly distributed. Put mixture in foil packet or 1-pint glass jar.
Store in cool, dry place and use within 3 to 4 months.
Makes about 3 tablespoons mix, enough for 3/4 cup dressing.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash
bananas.	Add
egg and oil; stir until mixture is smooth.
Add self-rising flour, while continuing to stir.
Add chopped nuts to the mixture.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at
for	1
hour or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted into the middle of the bread.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Divide into 4 sections.
Wrap in wax paper and chill overnight.
Cut into cookies.
Cook on foil-lined cookie sheet for 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Don't overcook, they are soft cookies.

title: short ribs - korean style
directions: Mix
all ingredients, except short ribs.
Soak ribs for about 1
hour.
Ribs
can
be
charcoal broiled or broiled in oven. Brush occasionally with remaining sauce.

title: stuffed artichokes-maltese
directions: In food processor, crumble bread; put aside.
Chop garlic, anchovies and olives.
Mix with bread and add capers and pepper (little salt) to taste.
Add olive oil until mixture is moist and easy to handle.

title: curried chicken with rice
directions: Prepare rice as label directs; keep warm.
Meanwhile, cut each chicken breast half into eight pieces.
In a cup, mix curry, bouillon, sugar and salt.

title: belgian cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage.
Add chopped onion and apple.
Saute in butter, then add the vinegar, water and sugar.
Mix well.
Serve hot.

title: cooked dried pinto beans
directions: Rinse and sort beans.
In large pot, put the water and dried beans.
Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Allow to stand, covered, for 1 hour.
Drain off soak water and rinse beans.
In pot, cook 1 hour.
Season with salt, Wesson oil and Bac*Os bits or season as you like.
Continue cooking 30 minutes.

title: spice cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients slowly, then
beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle on top of cake.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes.

title: fettucine
directions: Combine
first 5 ingredients and mix until creamy.
Add to cooked noodles and serve.

title: old fashion stack cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together. Add egg, molasses and buttermilk and mix well. Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and ginger together and add to other mixture. Roll real thin and bake.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into a ball and cover with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: coconut pineapple cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice and add enough water to make 1 cup.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add pineapple, coconut and juice to the other ingredients.
Beat on low speed for 1 minute.
Scrape bowl and beat two more minutes.
Pour in pan and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Frost with vanilla frosting and sprinkle with 1/2 cup nuts.

title: indonesian chicken sate
directions: Cut boned chicken into 3/4-inch cubes.
Thread 5 to 6 cubes onto each skewer.
Mix garlic, soya sauce and water.
Dip the threaded chicken pieces into this mixture.
Grill until meat is done, basting with oil to prevent drying out.
Turn several times. Do not overcook.
Serve with hot Peanut Sauce.

title: maple flavor molasses
directions: Bring all except egg whites just to a boil.
Take from stove, cool.
Add beaten egg whites, stir together until smooth.

title: quick finger paint
directions: Add tempera paint to liquid starch and stir.
Paint on glossy shelf paper or butcher paper.

title: travis's macaroni & cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until done.
Drain and add cheese.
Let melt. Stir in 1 c. milk.
Stir a couple of times to make sure the cheese is melted, add salt & pepper.

title: cheese spins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut shortening into flour mixture; stir in milk.
Turn out on floured board; knead lightly.
Roll out into a rectangle. Spread cheese over biscuit dough.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Cut into 1-inch slices and place on top of mixture in casserole (Beef-Garden Casserole).
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry ground meat and drain.
Fry bacon and drain.
Add onion, ketchup, mustard, both sugars, vinegar, pork and beans, kidney beans and butter lima beans.
Mix together.
Place in large baking pan and bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
(Can be kept warm in crock-pot.)

title: texas style corn bread
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Break in small pieces.
Cook mixture in heavy skillet 40 minutes in 400° oven.

title: wilted cucumbers
directions: * If you don't like it too hot, cut in half.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Top with whipped cream and shaved chocolate.
Wow!

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine tomatoes, onion, garlic, jalapeno pepper, cilantro, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Blend about 10 seconds or until the tomatoes are finely chopped.
Taste, adding more minced chili pepper if spicier flavor is desired. Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Serve with tacos, tostados or tortilla chips.
Makes 2 cups.

title: strawberry heart cake
directions: Cook according to directions and divide in one square pan and one circle pan.
Cut in half and make a heart.
Ice with white icing and you're done.

title: pizza dough
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, yeast, salt and sugar; mix well. Add water and shortening.
Let rest 15 minutes.
With well-floured or greased hands, press into 2 greased 12-inch pizza pans.
Top with your favorite sauce and toppings.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove and cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Continue to bake approximately 10 more minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Then add eggs.
Then add flour, sifted with soda and buttermilk alternately.
Mix well.
Add the vanilla and the bottom of red food coloring.
Bake in 3 layer cake pans at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: 3 minute microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir.
Check for thickness.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir and pour into buttered square pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: vegetable beef meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl combine meat, egg, bread crumbs,
soup
and water.
Shape into loaf and place in shallow baking
pan.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken pie with vegetables
directions: Boil chicken and pick off bone.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Heat broth, soup and onion for 10 minutes, stirring well.
Add vegetables to chicken in pan.
Add broth mixture.
Mix margarine, pepper, flour and buttermilk.
Spread batter over entire mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use 3 teaspoons in boiling water for a cup of tea.
Store in airtight container.

title: ranch chicken pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta salad as directed on package. Stir in remaining ingredients. Refrigerate or serve immediately. Garnish with fresh herbs. Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix together sugar, Jell-O and water, stir until dissolved, and add pineapple juice.
Pour into containers and freeze for at least 24 hr.
(Plastic milk jugs work well).
Take out of freezer at least 1 hr. before using.
Empty container into a large punch bowl; break mixture into chunks with a wooden spoon.
Add sprite or ginger ale; mix to a slushy consistency.
Makes a wonderful punch. Can add crushed pineapple or frozen strawberries when pouring in the pineapple juice.

title: heavenly banana bread
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. In another bowl, combine eggs, bananas, oil, buttermilk and vanilla; beat well. Add to flour mixture, stirring just until combined. Fold in nuts. Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until bread tests done. Cool on wire rack. Yield: 1 loaf.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute butter and onion; add rest of ingredients and heat through.
Put in casserole dish; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: homestyle creamed corn
directions: Cream the thawed whole kernel corn in a blender or food processor.
Pour into skillet and add remaining ingredients.
Cook until well blended.

title: primero mushroom bisque
directions: Melt butter in 6 to 8-quart Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add onion and celery.
Cover and cook until transparent, about 10 minutes; stir now and then.

title: uncle ben's wild rice casserole
directions: Cook
onion
and bell pepper in margarine.
Add pimento. Add cream
of mushroom soup and water.
Pour over rice and let set.

title: oven-fried chicken(from jane brody's good food book)
directions: Place chicken in shallow bowl; cover with milk.
Soak 15 minutes or longer (refrigerate to keep cold).
Put bread crumbs, cheese, parsley flakes and pepper in shallow bowl.
Coat soaked chicken pieces in the breading mixture.
Put on greased baking sheet.
Spray chicken lightly with vegetable oil spray (optional). Bake chicken in a preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts in food processor.
Mix everything together and bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: aunt alice's oven caramel corn
directions: Boil all ingredients (except corn) for 5 minutes, mixing well and stirring often.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Mix well; pour over popped corn and mix well.
Put into several large baking pans and place in 225° oven for 1 hour, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Place on wax paper to cool.
Break apart into large pieces; store in tightly closed container.

title: lime pickles
directions: Mix; pour over drained cucumbers.
Cook slowly for 2 hours and can them.
The pickles should look clear when done.
(Do not boil hard.)

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Scald the milk.
Let cool.
Add well beaten egg, sugar, flour and cocoa dissolved in hot water. Cook in double boiler until of creamy consistency.
Let cool. Add vanilla.
Beat with rotary beater. Serve with whipped cream.

title: louisiana mexican casserole
directions: Break tamales.
Layer ingredients in 1-quart casserole.
Put juice of tamales over all.
Bake about 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: pepperoni spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Combine spaghetti, sauce and pepperoni in 11 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot punch
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a large coffee maker.
Put spices in basket.
Perk like coffee.
Nice to serve during Christmas because of red color.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry cake roll
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs and add vanilla until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add 1/2 cup of sugar, beating until fluffy.
Fold in flour mixture.
Spread batter evenly in waxed paper-lined 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned, 10 to 12 minutes. Immediately loosen sides and turn onto a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Remove wax paper.
Starting at narrow end, roll cake and towel together.
Cool 30 minutes on rack.
Chill thoroughly.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: While cabbage is steaming, brown ground meat, onion, celery and bell pepper. Drain ground meat and add to cabbage.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix and simmer for 30 minutes on low heat.

title: old fashion molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add other ingredients in order given.
Work to soften dough.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Roll to about 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes and bake in moderate oven, 400° for about 10 minutes.
Great recipe for cut out cookies.

title: bobbie's lemon pie
directions: Mix the Kool-Aid with 1/2 of the Cool Whip. Blend real good. Pour into the graham cracker crust. Top with the other half of the Cool Whip.

title: apple streusel muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Sift together flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut in butter. Reserve 1/2 cup of the mixture for crumb topping. Stir together apple and 1/2 teaspoon lemon zest.

Add egg and milk; blend this with flour mixture, stirring lightly until evenly moist. Spoon into 12 greased medium-size muffin cups. Blend reserved crumb mixture with 1/2 teaspoon lemon zest, walnuts and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Sprinkle over batter and bake until toothpick or wire tester comes out clean, about 20 minutes.

title: "home made" potato soup
directions: Rub garlic in bottom of 1 wooden bowl.
Add olive oil and mix with garlic.
Take anchovies, chop them into small pieces and rub them into the bottom of the bowl.
Mix vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco and egg yolks.
Add lettuce and toss.
Add lemon juice.
Add Parmesan cheese and cracked black pepper to taste.
Top with Parmesan cheese and croutons.
Enjoy with a bottle of good white wine.

title: pickles
directions: Put pickles, peppers and onion in a bowl.
Mix sugar, salt, celery seed and vinegar. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over pickles and put in refrigerator.
Leave for 24 hours.
Will last a long time.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix all ingredients and boil for 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over 2 gallons popped corn. Preheat oven to 250°; cook for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: flour tortillas appetizer
directions: Mix and spread in flour shells.
Refrigerate and then cut into 1/2-inch circles.

title: banana pops
directions: You will need ice cream popsicles sticks.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, onion, both cheeses and 1 cup of sour cream in large bowl.
Place into greased casserole or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread 2nd cup of sour cream over top.
Crush tube of Ritz crackers and sprinkle over sour cream.
Drizzle melted oleo over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture; beat well.
Reserve 1/2 cup batter.
Spread remaining batter in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread cherry pie filling over batter. Drop reserved batter by teaspoon over cherry filling.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Serve warm or cool topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: school house rolls
directions: Mix yeast, milk, sugar, oil and salt together.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Use mixer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let work until double in size.
Then roll out and cut.
Then let work in a bread pan until double in size.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: scalloped noodles
directions: Boil noodles until done.
Drain water.
Mix together noodles and puree.
Layer in dish the noodle mixture, cheese, salt and pepper until you get to top of dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: tart ole
directions: Mash the cream cheese.
Spread on bottom of a 9-inch quiche or pie plate.
Layer rest of ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with corn or tortilla chips.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix dressing with oleo. Put 1/2 of dressing in 9 x 13 pan. Save the rest for the top. Mix rest of ingredients together and spread over the layer of dressing. Put other 1/2 of dressing on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese pie
directions: Combine sugar and melted butter.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: red hot salad
directions: Boil 7-Up to melt red hots.
Add gelatin and applesauce. Chill to mold.

title: broiled tomatoes with mozzarella
directions: Preheat oven to broil.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Place tomatoes in a single layer on the cookie sheet.
Place a slice of Mozzarella cheese on top of each tomato slice, letting part of the tomato show.
Mix together the last 5 ingredients; drizzle over the tomatoes and cheese.
Place under broiler for 5 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine bread crumbs, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese.
Melt margarine.
Dip chicken breasts in melted margarine and then roll in crumb mixture.
Place breasts in a shallow casserole dish that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake covered at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove cover and let brown for approximately 10 minutes. Serves 4.

title: sweet 'n sour drumettes
directions: Put 3 pounds chicken drumettes in a single layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake, uncovered, for 2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn, mix together place in casserole dish. Mix soup, sour cream, cheese and water chestnuts.
Spread over beans and corn.
Melt margarine mix in crushed crackers, spread on top of casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add 1 can of corn or beans extra if needed.

title: spinach artichoke casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease casserole dish. Cook spinach and artichoke hearts according to directions on packages. Drain well. To cooked spinach, add butter, cream cheese and lemon juice. Blend together. Place artichoke hearts that have been quartered or halved into bottom of greased casserole dish; add spinach mixture. Top with cracker crumbs or stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: noodle kugel (jewish soul food)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook noodles in salted water until just done. Rinse and cool in cold water.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients as you would for a cake; sprinkle top with dots of butter.
Mix cinnamon and brown sugar together and sprinkle over dough.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Drizzle confectioners glaze over all when cool.
Nuts may be added on top of glaze.
Serve warm with hot coffee.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine and mix cake mix and eggs.
Stir in cherry pie filling.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage.
Drain well; put back in pan. Add spices.
Melt in cheese.
Spread on rye bread; broil approximately 5 minutes.

title: chicken-baked pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper both sides of meat; brown slowly on both sides in fat.
Drain fat from skillet.
Combine soup, milk and water. Pour around chops in skillet.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until chops are tender.
Serve hot.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Beat egg until frothy; beat in sugar and butter and cream until fluffy.
Add sour cream and vanilla; blend well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to sour cream mixture.
Blend well. Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar topping evenly over batter.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cheesy corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Fry bacon, drain, and crumble. In a casserole dish combine all ingredients and mix well. Bake for 40 minutes and stir once.

title: butterscotch treats
directions: Put butterscotch chips and peanut butter on low heat or in double boiler and melt.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies. Spread into buttered baking sheet.
Refrigerate until cool.
This treat is better if kept cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil in large bowl.
Add eggs, bananas and sour cream; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well at low speed.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in 9x13 greased
pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: barber cups
directions: Brown hamburger meat until brown; drain.
Add barbecue sauce. Heat until hot.
Take one can of biscuits, roll out flat; put in muffin pan.
Fill with hamburger meat and a piece of cheese.
Put in oven and bake until brown.

title: black beans(could also use small brown beans.)
directions: Rinse beans and place in large pot. To 1 pound of beans (2 cups), add 6 to 8 cups of cold water. Let stand overnight or at least 6 to 8 hours. Drain, soak water and rinse beans. Add 6 cups cold water, salt and garlic salt to beans. Saut chopped onions. Add to beans. Bring to boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer about 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Within 30 minutes of desired bean tenderness, add sausage. Serve over rice.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix Worcestershire sauce and cream cheese.
Mold in dish and refrigerate.
Mix together chili sauce, ketchup, horseradish and lemon juice.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Flake crab over chili sauce mixture.
Serve with crackers.

title: surprise english walnut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar to eggs while beating.
Beat until light and thick.
Add salt, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cover with whipped cream when cool.
This pie is delicious but it is not pretty without the whipped cream.

title: ima's salsa
directions: Brown meat; add other ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Press crescent rolls into 13 x 9-inch pan until bottom and half of sides is covered.
Beat cream cheese and sour cream together; add sugar and vanilla.
Beat eggs in one at a time, beating well after each one.
Pour over crescent rolls in pan. Sprinkle with raisins and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not grease pan.
After cake is cooled, place in refrigerator.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in greased baking dish. Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes.

title: potato wedges
directions: Slice each potato into 8 slices and arrange skin side down in baking pan.
In small bowl combine remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 400°, basting occasionally, for 45 minutes.

title: roy's chili
directions: Braise meat, add onions, then add tomatoes, sauce and beans. Stir and cook on low.
Then add chili mix and powder.
Cook for 1 to 2 hours on lowest heat you have.
Wash 1 lb of Ball Park wieners.
Put in your chili and when the chili is ready to eat the hot dogs will be too.

title: grape bavarian
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water, add grape juice. Chill until slightly thickened.

title: skillet pork chops and rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil.
Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper; brown on both sides.
Remove chops.
Add water, brown sugar, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cans of tomato sauce.
Stir, bringing to boiling point.
Add rice and stir.
Return chops to pan.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Pour remaining tomato sauce on chops; cover and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frozen oreo pie
directions: Mix 3/4 of cookie crumbs, Cool Whip and softened ice cream together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Sprinkle the rest of the cookie crumbs on top.
Freeze overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease and flour 1 large or 2 small loaf pans.
In large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, blending well. Add the bananas, flour, baking soda, vanilla and nuts; mix well. Pour the batter into prepared pan.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour, or until brown.
Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Pour into uncooked tart shells. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until shell becomes brown.

title: bean and beef casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; add onions and bacon while meat is still browning.
Drain.
Add pork and beans and ketchup.
Let simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: apple oatmeal bars
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add brown sugar and oats.
Work in butter.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and spread mix on the bottom of pan.
Put the apples on and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mix. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve warm with cream or ice cream or cut and serve like brownies.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend ingredients and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll out dough and cut into 2 or 2 1/2-inch squares.
Fill each square with filling and fold into a triangle.
Bake according to package directions.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken (make broth from these items).
Slice meat in short, narrow strips.
Slice vegetables. Saute chicken in oil until meat is lightly browned.
Add to chicken the vegetables and fry a few minutes, until vegetables are wilted.
Mix broth, soy sauce, sugar, salt and pepper; pour over mixture.
Cover and steam 5 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in water; add to broth and stir until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: fudgy brownies(quick, low saturated fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir cocoa and baking soda in mixing bowl.
Blend in 1/3 cup oil.
Stir in boiling water until mixture thickens.
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup oil.
Blend until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Blend completely. Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan or two 8-inch square pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for 13 x 9-inch pan or 30 to 32 minutes for 8-inch square pans.
Cool before cutting.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Heat oven to 350° (night or morning).
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Slowly beat in sugar until soft peaks form.
Beat in vanilla to firm peaks.
Gently fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
(May be close together as they will not run.)
Place in oven; turn off heat.
Do not open oven door.
Leave in all night; will be completely baked following morning.
(Color with food coloring, if desired.)

title: tuna shortcake
directions: Blend soup and milk.
Add tuna, peas and pimientos.
Heat and stir often.
Serve over toast or biscuits.

title: dill crackers
directions: Blend all ingredients, but crackers.
Pour over crackers and let stand for 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Keep container covered.
Store in airtight containers.

title: mushroom pork chops
directions: Roll chops in flour.
Heat oil in skillet.
Fry chops until golden brown.
Mix milk and soup in a deep baking pan.
Place chops in pan in soup and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, pork, onion, chopped fine pepper, tomato sauce, eggs and garlic salt together.
Mix oats and cracker crumbs together with 1/2 cup milk.
Put in with the rest.
Mix all together.
Put in pan.
Pour tomato juice over it and cook at 350°.

title: apple cake with caramelscotch frosting
directions: Combine first four ingredients in mixing bowl.
Sift together next three ingredients and add to oil mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Gradually stir in hot milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture coats a spoon.

title: macadamia biscotti
directions: Mix flour and baking powder together, set aside.
Beat sugar and margarine until fluffy add to baking powder, flour mixture. Add one egg at a time in.
Add extracts.
Mix well.
With a large spoon, stir in one can macadamia nuts.
Form batter into 2 inch loaves around 1-2 inch x 3 inch width x 15 inch length each on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until golden.
Remove trays and cool for 10-15 minutes and reduce oven to 250°.
Slice loaves into 1/2 inch slices.
Place them standing up on tray and return to oven for 30-40 minutes.
Turn off oven and let them sit there for 1 hour or two, so they are crunchy with no chewy ness. Store in airtight container.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and add light corn syrup and sugar (with salt added to it).
Add butter, flour and vanilla.
Beat until mixture becomes frothy.
Add pecans and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: quick baked pasta family style
directions: Bring 4 quarts water to boil.
Heat a large frying pan and add the oil, beef and garlic.
Saute until meat is tender and then drain off excess fat.
Add all remaining ingredients, except the cheese (for topping) and the pasta.
Simmer the mixture while the pasta cooks until just barely tender.
Drain the pasta and mix it with the sauce.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugars, cocoa, flour and salt in a medium saucepan. Add milk, butter and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until boiling; cook 5 minutes.
Cool; stir in vanilla.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir baking soda in buttermilk. Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Knead dough on a floured service several times.
Return dough to lightly greased bowl and cover with plastic wrap.
Let set overnight.
Pinch off small amounts of dough and form into balls.
Place in greased muffin pans and let rise.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.
Dough will keep refrigerated 5 to 7 days.

title: hawaiian wing ding casserole
directions: Measure 2 cups pineapple juice from pineapple in saucepan. combine liquid with vinegar, soy sauce, chicken bouillon and sugar.
Stir and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Add arrow root and simmer until sauce thickens.
Add tomatoes, pineapple and green pepper.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Fry wing dings in hot oil until crispy.

title: rice casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, melt butter. Add raw rice, soup, onion and mushrooms.
Stir all ingredients together. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and crackers.
Pour into greased 11 x 7-inch pan.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: diabetic applesauce cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, egg, applesauce and spices.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Add to applesauce mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Bring to boil vinegar, beet liquid, sugar, cloves, salt, peppercorns and bay leaf.
Pour over beets.
Chill.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook all 4 types of pasta according to package directions; drain and set aside. Brown ground beef until done and drain excess fat; set aside.
Cut pepperoni into slices, then quarters. Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Place in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan or two 8 x 8-inch pans.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese is golden.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: melting moments
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat well.
Gradually add flour and cornstarch, beating until smooth.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cookies do not brown on top.
Cool slightly on cookie sheets. Frost with Lemon Frosting.
Makes about 9 dozen.

title: stuffed pepper pie
directions: In large saucepan, bring 2 quarts water to rolling boil.
Place peppers in boiling water and cook for 15 minutes.
Drain; arrange, cut side up, around bottom of ungreased pie pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
In same saucepan, combine 1 cup water and margarine.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat; stir in potato flakes, milk and egg. Mix well.
Stir in sausage; spoon into pepper lined pan.
Arrange tomato wedges on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well with hands.
Shape into small balls or press into mini muffin tin.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar-free fruit and nut muffins
directions: Place dates, prunes, raisins and water in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Take off the stove and add stick of margarine.
Set aside to cool.
Then add beaten eggs, salt, vanilla and soda.
Add flour and nuts last.
Bake in miniature muffin tins or a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish for 30 minutes at 300°. This freezes real well.

title: cherry brunch cake
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and cream cheese in large bowl. Mix at low speed until fine crumbs form.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
To remaining crumbs, add water and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed of mixer.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Spoon pie filling over batter.
Gently spread to cover batter.
Combine reserved crumbs and chopped pecans.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until set in center and edges are golden brown.
Cool 25 minutes, then glaze.

title: yogurt and whipped cream pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and yogurt together. Place into graham cracker crust. Heat mixed berries in small bowl in microwave, about 2 to 3 minutes. Use sugar or Splenda to sweeten. Wait until berries cool and drop across the top of pie. Spoon the juice over top and sides of pie. Put into freezer until frozen and then cut into slices and serve.

title: black-eyed pea cakes
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour, covered.
Shape into 1/2-inch patties.
Coat with yellow cornmeal and cook approximately 2 minutes on each side in olive oil (approximately 1/2 cup).
Makes approximately 10 patties.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix flour, cinnamon and nutmeg and set aside.
Mix sugar and oil; add eggs.
Mix real well and add water.
Add flour and mix well; then add pecans and fold in bananas.
Bake in oven at 350° in Bundt pan for 1 hour or loaf pans for 45 minutes.

title: mama graves' rice
directions: Melt butter in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients and stir gently to mix.
Bake for 1 hour in 375° oven.

title: sue may's potato salad
directions: Cook 5 to 6 medium-size potatoes until done.
Use no seasoning while cooking.
Drain potatoes and add all ingredients, mixing well.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze. Can freeze in small plastic cups or paper cups for children or in desert bowls for brunch. Take out of freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: brickle dip
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Soak apple slices overnight in pineapple juice.
Use this dip for fresh, firm apples, sliced.

title: sweet nothings
directions: Melt together margarine, peanut butter and butterscotch morsels.
Pour mixture over Rice Chex; coat well.
Pour powdered sugar into paper bag.
Drop Corn Chex into bag and shake well. Cool and dry on baking sheet.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: roasted fresh vegetables
directions: Prepare vegetables by washing and cutting large vegetables into chunks.
Toss vegetables in olive oil combined with herbs, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Place vegetables that require longer cooking time, such as potatoes, in a baking dish and place in either an oven preheated to 425° or a hot grill.
Roast about 15 minutes, then add other vegetables throughout remaining cooking time (about 45 minutes), according to their required cooking time for tenderness.

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix 1/4 cup sugar, egg, butter, flour, milk, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Fold in apple with additional 1/4 cup sugar. Bake in greased muffin tins for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: orange dream cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool.
Combine powdered sugar and milk; drizzle over cake. Decorate with sprinkles.

title: low calorie salad
directions: Wash and drain cottage cheese.
Drain pineapple. Mix dry jello into whipped topping until crystals are dissolved.
Fold pineapple and cottage cheese into jello mixture.
Spread into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix in order by hand.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: caramelized rum bananas
directions: 1. Butter a baking dish with 1 Tbsp. of the butter, or use solid margarine, not the soft diet type.

title: the famous currant cookies(aka cereal cookies)
directions: Mix flour, sugars and eggs.
Add cereal, oats, currants and coconut.
In small bowl mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to cereal mixture. Mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: herbed french bread
directions: Cut bread diagonally at 1/2-inch intervals.
Beat butter or margarine until fluffy.
Add crushed herbs and a sprinkle of onion powder.
Spread about 2 teaspoons on each slice.
Reassemble loaf and wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate fruit drops
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg.
Beat well.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Makes approximately 4 1/2 dozen.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Place
potatoes
in crock-pot.	Layer chicken pieces on top. Cover
with
Italian
dressing.
Start
on high and turn down after 30 minutes.
Cook 6 to 8 hours on low.

title: tressies' applesauce cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and heat until oleo is melted. Let cool. Mix all ingredients and put into well-greased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Combine eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Beat until well mixed.
Stir in flour.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over lard.
When melted, add sugar, salt, milk and beaten eggs.
Crumble yeast into this and mix well.
Add potatoes and 2 to 3 cups flour.
Add flour by cupful until mixture is fairly stiff.
Put into large, greased bowl.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Two hours before baking, punch down. Make into rolls.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked tuna stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash potatoes, rub skins with margarine; prick with fork.
Bake on oven rack 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: creamy baked chicken breast
directions: Put chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine soup and water; spoon over chicken and top with cheese.
Sprinkle stuffing mix and drizzle oleo over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese straws
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Melt butter; let cool.
Pour over cheese; toss gently.
Add to dry ingredients; cut in until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle water evenly over flour mixture.
Stir with a fork until all ingredients are moistened; shape into a ball.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface; cut into 3 x 1/3-inch strips.
Place strips on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until crisp.
Place on wire racks to cool.

title: steamed suet pudding
directions: Stir ingredients together and steam in a covered dish or pail, with cover on, for 3 hours.
Keep water boiling.
When done, remove from water and put or turn out on plate.
A knife warmed and inserted between dish and pudding will help loosen it to make it come out easier.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Lightly grease two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans; coat each with 1 tablespoon cornmeal.
Mix 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda in a large bowl.

title: baked stuffed zucchini
directions: Boil split zucchini 15 minutes in 1/2 cup salted water. Drain.
Scoop out pulp and save, leaving clean cavity.
Arrange zucchini shells in oblong baking dish.

title: wassail
directions: Combine juices and spices.
Bring to a simmer, strain and serve hot.
Makes 16 servings.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In 10 x 6-inch baking dish, arrange broccoli.
Top with meat.
In small bowl, mix soup and milk; pour over meat.
Sprinkle with cheese.
In cup, combine bread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until hot and bubbling.
Makes 4 servings.

title: butternut squash
directions: Layer sliced squash; add next 3 ingredients.
Put sliced apple on top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: yeast rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, add 1 cup warm water and sugar.
In a small bowl, dissolve dry yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add yeast to sugar and water and mix.
Add salt, shortening and egg.
Add the flour, 1 cup at a time until dough becomes workable.
Knead dough, let rise until doubled.
Form into rolls and place in a baking dish; let rise again.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Pat tops with butter.

title: stir-fried broccoli and mushrooms
directions: In a large skillet (or wok), heat corn oil over medium heat. Add onion and garlic. Stir-fry for about 1/2 minute.
Add broccoli, mushrooms, salt and pepper; stir-fry for about 5 minutes or so or until tender and crispy.
May add sliced or diced green bell peppers, if desired.

title: upside-down french toast
directions: Melt butter in 9-inch square baking pan.
Into butter stir brown sugar and pineapple (drained of almost all syrup).
Spread this mix evenly over bottom of pan.
Beat egg, milk and salt together until soft.
Layer over pineapple and sugar in pan.
Bake 25 minutes in 400° preheated oven or until lightly browned.
Cool 1 minute before inverting on plate.

title: crock-pot turkey
directions: Remove skin from turkey breasts and wash thoroughly.
Sprinkle heavily with pepper.
Coat with Texas Pete sauce and wrap in aluminum foil.
Place in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.

title: sticky buns
directions: Thaw, but
do
not let bread raise.
Break 1 loaf up in the bottom
of greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Melt oleo.
Then add brown
sugar,
pudding
mix,
milk and cinnamon.
Mix all together,
then
pour over broken bread.
Break second loaf on top and
let rise for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well with just enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Serve with lettuce or as desired.

title: meat loaf surprise log
directions: Combine diced pineapple and tomatoes in a draining bowl to drain juice.
Once dried, mix with green pepper and set aside. Take hamburger and split in half.
With the 1 pound of hamburger, knead.
Punch a "ditch" in the center of it.
Pour the mixture in the ditch.
Put the other pound of kneaded hamburger on the top and roll in egg.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Will feed 8 to 12 adults.

title: egg pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In blender mix all ingredients well. Melt 3 tablespoons butter in oblong casserole dish or pie pan. Pour batter in , then bake 20 minutes.
Serve with warm syrup.

title: vegetable pizza bars
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet with sheets of crescent roll dough, patting and stretching to fit.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
In mixing bowl, combine salad dressing, sour cream and dressing mix.
Spread over crust.
Combine vegetables, tossing to mix and distribute evenly over cheese mixture. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over the top.
Cover with Saran Wrap and push vegetables into the cheese.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Cut in small bars.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: mock sauerbraten(pot roast)
directions: Sear meat on all sides in Crisco in Dutch oven or similar pot. Add all ingredients.
Leave carrots whole or cut in half.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove carrots, cloves and bay leaves and add flour paste to thicken sauce.
Mixture will make about 1 quart sauce or gravy.
Slice meat thin.

title: one-pan tomato basil chicken
directions: In a large skillet, saute rice-vermicelli mix as the package directs.
Stir in 2 cups water, chicken and contents of seasoning packet.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Cover; reduce heat to low. Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in broccoli, tomato and basil.
Cover; simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until most of liquid is absorbed. Sprinkle with cheese, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: awesome potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns and mix with melted butter.
Mix sour cream, soup, Cheddar and onion.
Mix with potatoes.
Place into 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
You can also bake with crushed corn flakes on top.

title: pineapple sweet potato bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1-quart casserole.
In medium bowl, mash sweet potatoes with margarine and salt.
Add pineapple and orange juice.
Blend well.
Spoon into greased casserole. Sprinkle with brown sugar and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix and chill.
In double boiler, melt 3/4 stick wax and 16 ounces chocolate chips.
Take chilled mix and form into 1-inch balls.
With toothpick, insert or dip each ball into wax mix. Place on foil to set.
When finished, put in airtight container and keep in cool storage.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients.
Let set at least 2 hours.
Mix this with romaine lettuce.
Then add cheeses.
Add lemon juice.
Add croutons.
Toss and serve.

title: basil scalloped potatoes
directions: To Make Sauce:
In small saucepan, melt the butter.
Stir in flour, salt, basil and pepper.
Stir in milk all at once.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Stir in the 1/2 cup parsley.

title: beef stroganoff supreme
directions: Cut meat in strips, 1/4-inch wide.
Brown quickly in 1/4 cup butter.
Push meat to one side.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Cook just until tender.
Add broth.
Heat just to boiling.
Blend sour cream and flour.
Stir into broth.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Season to taste.
Serve over hot Baptist Rice.
Serves 4 or 5. A good party dish!

title: aunt ruth's creamed potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until easily stuck with a fork.
Cool. Cut into cubes.
Set aside in a bowl.
Make white sauce.
Season with salt, pepper, green onion and herbs.
Add more to taste. Stir sauce over potatoes and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apple filling in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over apples.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: olympic chicken
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients well.
Marinate chicken in mixture for 1 hour.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain off water from vegetables.
Cook vinegar, sugar and oil. Bring to boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over vegetables.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Place sugar, margarine and evaporated milk in heavy saucepan. Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Cook to soft ball stage on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter chips, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in buttered 9-inch square or larger pan.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooked chicken.
Mix two soups and milk together and pour over meat.
Mix together stuffing and melted butter and sprinkle over chicken.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, covered, then uncover and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: cookie salad
directions: * Can use 1 cup buttermilk and 1 cup regular milk if desired.

title: south of the border chicken casserole
directions: Boil whole chicken and remove meat.
Saute 1 large bell pepper and 1 medium onion in oil.
In a bowl, combine 1 can cream of mushroom, 1 can cream of chicken and 1 can of milk.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Put all ingredients, except pie crust, into blender for approximately 15 seconds.
Pour in frozen pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Then lower temperature to 350° for 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: chilli con queso
directions: Brown onions in butter 5 minutes. Stir in chillies, tomatoes, salt and pepper. Simmer until most of the liquid is evaporated. Stir in cheese. Stir until melted. Serve with chips for dipping. Can be fixed in crock-pot.

title: polish cabbage rolls
directions: Combine beef, rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Steam cabbage whole until leaves pull off easily (only a few leaves will pull off at a time).
Place cabbage back over steam until all are removed.
Place small leaves in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Roll 1 to 3 tablespoons of mixture in each leaf.
Place seams down in pan.
Pour tomato sauce or tomatoes (if using whole tomatoes, add 1/2 cup water) over cabbage rolls.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Keep check; do not let cook dry.
Add water, if necessary.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Saute garlic, onion and bread crumbs in oil for 2 minutes. Mix constantly.
Remove from flame.
Add clams using about 2/3 liquid.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with plain crackers.

title: raspberry dream bars
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder in bowl; cut in butter until crumbly.
Add 2 eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla; mix well.
Press over bottom of pan and 1 inch up sides of buttered 10 x 16-inch baking pan.
Spread preserves over dough.
Beat 2 eggs, 1 teaspoon vanilla and remaining 3 ingredients in bowl; spread over the preserves. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: holiday punch
directions: Chill all juices and ginger ale.
Mix juices and sugar. Add ginger ale just before serving.
Ice cubes
made
of additional pineapple juice or a frozen fruit ring
are
easy
and pretty additions.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Combine everything but chips until well blended.
Stir in chips.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marble squares
directions: Combine cream cheese and 1/3 cup sugar in medium size mixer bowl.
Mix well and add 1 egg.
Mix and set aside.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine and cook over medium heat about 15 minutes or until peanuts pop.
As soon as peanuts start popping, add 2 teaspoons soda and stir well.
Pour immediately in well buttered pan. (Don't pat or level out.)

title: bran-sunflower nut bread
directions: Grease 2 (8 1/2 x 2 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Mix 2 cups flour, sugar, cereal, salt and yeast.
Heat water, milk, molasses or honey and 1/4 cup olive oil to 125° to 130°.
Stir into flour mixture.
Beat on low speed 1 minute, then on medium speed 1 minute.
Stir in nuts and remaining flour, one cup at a time.

title: karen's macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain well.
Combine with cheese, peas, celery and onion.
Combine mayo, milk, salt, parsley, sugar and pepper.
Stir in vinegar.
Add to macaroni.
Mix well.
Cover; chill thoroughly.
Stir gently before serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, boiling water and shortening; let cool.
Add eggs and flour; mix well.
Knead and roll out 1/4 to 1/3-inch thick.
Cut into dumpling size.
Dip each piece into the melted butter.
Distribute in 2 Bundt pans and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes. Dump out and wrap in foil paper.
Eat with honey while hot.
This recipe may be cut in half if only one loaf is desired.

title: mini pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage together; drain well.
Cut Velveeta cheese into cubes; melt in with meat.
Add oregano and garlic salt; cook on low until cheese is melted.
Spread on rye bread; place on cookie sheet.
Place in broiler for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: buttered microwave potatoes
directions: Melt butter with onion in microwave on high for 1 minute. Stir in potatoes. Sprinkle with season salt. Cover and microwave on high for 8-9 minutes. Stirring 2-3 times until tender.

title: peanut butter pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: sunburst salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water; add 2 1/4 cups cold water and drained pineapple.
Put in a large, flat pan.
Add a layer of sliced bananas, then a layer of small marshmallows.
Set until firm.

title: texas style barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a pan.
Bring to a boil.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
This is enough to baste 4 to 5 chickens.

title: krispy chocolate caramel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In medium bowl, combine flour and powdered sugar. Using pastry blender or fork, cut in margarine until crumbly. Lightly press mixture in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Mix and bake in large pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orzo casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook orzo in boiling, salted water for 8 minutes.
Drain, but don't rinse.
Cut butter into small chunks. Put orzo and butter into a casserole dish and stir until butter melts.
Add remaining ingredients; stir and cover.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add carrot strips.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until carrots are glazed or heated through.

title: boiled chocolate cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; add salt and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil 3 minutes, then add the oats, peanut butter, margarine and vanilla.
Mix real well, then spoon onto wax paper.
Let cool. Enjoy!

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Blend in egg yolk and vanilla. Add cake mix (dry), 1/3 at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Mix the last third by hand.
Cover; chill 30 minutes. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from sheet.

title: angel delight
directions: Crumble cake
in
a
9 x 13-inch dish.	Mix Eagle Brand milk, almond
extract, pudding and water together.
Chill for about 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour over crumbled cake. Chill for several
hours. Before serving, top with cherry pie filling.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Melt cocoa and butter in sauce pan. Keep heat low, stirring constantly. Cool slightly. Add eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla. Beat until smooth. Pour into pie pan (no crust). Bake at 350° for 25 - 30 minutes. Serve hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: wine biscuits
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Roll in 1-inch balls, then into strips. Twist and shape.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet to cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Whip cream with sugar and vanilla. Crush walnuts in a plastic bag and roll with rolling pin. Add to cream. Add drained fruit. Mix well and chill for 30 minutes before serving.

title: john mazetti
directions: Saute together ground beef, onions and green pepper.
Add mushrooms, soup, noodles and cream cheese. Mix well and put into a large casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake one hour, uncovered, at 350°.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: red and green bean salad
directions: Cook beans in 1 quart of boiling water until crisp and tender, about 8 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water to stop cooking. Drain again.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and bring to boil.
Let cool until lukewarm.
Stir warm water and yeast together.
Mix with first mixture and add a small package of all-purpose flour.
Stir together and mix well.
Cover and let rise in a warm place.
Add salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Mix well and put in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: guacamole supreme
directions: Halve and pit avocados; scoop out meat into large bowl.
Add lemon juice.
Mash until almost smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients except chips.
Bury avocado pit in center; cover with plastic wrap.
Chill no longer than 4 hours.
Remove pit before serving.
Serve with chips.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt margarine and gently stir in all ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: jenna's soup
directions: Mix meat with salt and pepper; shape into balls.
Put oil in Dutch oven and heat.
Add meat and onion.
Cook until meat is well browned and onion is tender.
Drain.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour 1/2 cup oil and vinegar dressing over chicken. Bake uncovered 20 minutes.
Remove chicken from baking dish.
Put 2/3 cup rice, broccoli, carrots and water chestnuts in dish.
Fix 1 3/4 cups water and chicken bouillon.
Pour over rice and vegetables.
Place chicken on top of rice and vegetables and bake 45 minutes.

title: mexican cabbage
directions: Brown first four ingredients together in a Dutch oven.
Drain off excess grease.
Add soup, Ro-Tel and tomatoes, then add shredded cabbage, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix well with wire whisk and fry.
Makes 10 to 15 pancakes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 of water, sugar and salt.
Add half of flour, then add egg, shortening and the rest of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Cover with cloth; let rise.
Make into rolls and let rise again (2 hours).
Makes 4 dozen rolls.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Brown chicken
in
small
amount of oil.
Chop the bell peppers, onion and	garlic	and add to browned chicken.
Saute until onions are clear.
Add chicken and beef broth.
Bring to a boil and add salt,	pepper and red pepper to taste.
Cook on medium-high for 30 to 45 minutes.
Turn off heat and add flour and water
mixture
to
thicken
mixture.
Serve
over
rice. Serves 4.

title: ravioli and sun-dried tomato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Season to taste.
Add a small amount of olive oil or oil from sun-dried tomatoes to season salad.

title: * mexicali casserole *
directions: Line bottom of a 1-quart casserole with 1/2 cup corn chips. Spread chili over the chips.
Add corn and onion.
Cover with remaining corn chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove cover and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: patty's mushroom salad
directions: Mix all salad ingredients together except anchovies.

title: hot dogs wrapped in bacon
directions: Cut hot dogs into 4 pieces.

title: ambrosia candy
directions: Stir all together; put in shallow pan.
Bake until bubbly for about 12 to 15 minutes at 300°.
Remove from oven.
Stir in 1 box confectioners sugar.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper or foil.

title: glazed citrus sections
directions: Section grapefruit halves, leaving outside shells intact. Discard the membrane.
Reserve the grapefruit shells.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Stir butter into hot spaghetti. Stir in Parmesan and egg.
Form into crust in buttered 10-inch pie pan.
Cook ground beef and onion until tender; drain off fat. Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Heat through.
Spread cottage cheese over crust. Then pour in tomato and beef mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 5 minutes more until cheese melts.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix everything together, but the Bac*Os, ahead of time.
Put the Bac*Os in just before serving.

title: louise's orange pound cake
directions: Mix and bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: harvest cake
directions: Dice apples and add sugar; set aside for an hour.
Add raisins to apples.
Allow raisins to get plump.
Beat eggs.
Add oil and vanilla.
Pour over apple mixture.
In a separate bowl mix together flour, soda and spices and add to mixture.
Stir thoroughly.
Add nuts and stir again.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sauteed zucchini and onions
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In bowl, combine first 5 ingredients; set aside. In large bowl, with mixer at medium-high, beat eggs 2 minutes. Add both sugars; beat until well combined.
Beat in pumpkin, butter and juice until blended.
At low speed, gradually add flour mixture, mixing only until blended.

title: enriched oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Sift flour, measure, then sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Flour raisins with a small amount of the mixture. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk. Add baby oatmeal.
Mix well.
Dough will be stiff.
Add raisins.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful onto greased baking sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown in 400° oven.
Allow to cool slightly before removing from pan.
Makes about 40 cookies, 2 1/2-inches in diameter.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook lima beans in salted water with cover until done.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour beans in covered casserole.
Place slice of ham or Canadian bacon on top, if desired.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Combine tomatoes and onions with water and salt in crock or bowl; soak for 3 hours.
Drain and rinse thoroughly with cold water.
Combine remaining ingredients and boil for 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and onions; bring to a boil and simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Pack into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 2 or 2 1/2 pints.

title: butter cookies
directions: Have butter and egg at room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add flour, one cup at a time. Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Press flat.

title: 10 minute german sweet chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons milk over low heat, stirring until melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese; add remaining milk and chocolate mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Freeze about 4 hours.
Garnish with chocolate curls.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese with mixer.
Mix all other ingredients together and add to sugar and cream mixture.
Freeze. Keep frozen until ready to use.
Use 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Do not preheat oven.
Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream and vanilla to sugar mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix sugar with cinnamon.
In a well-greased and floured pan, place 1/3 batter, cinnamon sugar, 1/3 batter, cinnamon sugar then 1/3 batter.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
When cool, dust with confectioners sugar or drizzle with thin icing.

title: tasty cauliflower
directions: Boil cauliflower in salty water until tender. Pour dressing and cheese over it. Bake until melted.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in baking dish.
Add hash browns, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, soup and onion.
Mix corn flakes and 1/2 stick melted butter together and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate delight cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and confectioners sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Combine chocolate, hot water and vanilla in saucepan.
Heat until chocolate melts, stirring constantly.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Remove and reserve 3 cups chocolate mixture.
Add oil, eggs, flour, salt, soda and buttermilk to remaining chocolate mixture; mix well.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until layers test done.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Spread reserved chocolate mixture between layers and over top and side of cake.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: mary beth's buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs, one at a time.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add alternately with flour to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Add extract. pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour and 20 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer chicken, broth and soup.

title: blueberry or cherry cream pie
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip.
Add lemon juice and stir.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Spoon fruit on top.
Chill.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and mash avocado.
Add salt and lemon juice.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve with corn chips.

title: chow chow pickles
directions: First Day:
Place 2 gallons cucumbers in a glass, stone or enamel vessel. Cover with 1 gallon boiling water to which 3 cups salt has been added.

title: snack cake mix
directions: Mix all together.
Store in 2 1/4 cup packages.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to box directions and drain.
Melt butter.
Add flour gradually to make paste.
Add milk, a little at a time, stirring constantly.
Add salt and heat until medium thick.
Add grated cheese to sauce and heat until cheese melts. Pour drained macaroni into cheese sauce and microwave for 5 minutes on High.

title: cherry delight
directions: Cream the margarine and brown sugar.
Add flour and mix well. Stir in pecans.
Press mixture in bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool.

title: japanese fruit pie(2 pies)
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch pudding mix (dry) in pan (not instant pudding).
Cut dough into 12 pieces each.
Fold into rolls and lay in pan on pudding mix.
Melt brown sugar and butter with cinnamon.
Pour over dough and refrigerate overnight.
Take out 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt effie's chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly in a heavy iron skillet or saucepan.
Add milk and stir until well blended and smooth.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly to prevent sticking.
Remove from heat when thick (not as thick as pudding, but thicker than brown gravy).
Add margarine and vanilla.
Serve over hot homemade biscuits, pancakes or toast.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine eggs, soup, mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.
Add broccoli; mix well.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Melt margarine and combine with stuffing mix.
Mix well.
Sprinkle on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: country fried steak
directions: Divide steak into serving pieces.
Pound with a kitchen mallet or rim of saucer until thin.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dust with flour.
In a skillet, heat oil and sear meat until evenly browned on all sides.
Add onion and cook several minutes until limp.
Combine chicken stock and buttermilk and pour over meat. Stir to loosen up crust from the bottom of the skillet.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat until meat is tender, 45 to 50 minutes. Add cheese and stir into gravy.
This is delicious over rice or biscuits.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Marinate chicken pieces for 24 hours in the refrigerator. Lift pieces from marinade. Discard marinade. Put chicken in baking pan and cover. Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Take off cover. Broil 5 to 10 minutes, uncovered, so the chicken will brownish red but not dark. Serve with hot boiled rice. Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini stuffed tomatoes
directions: Slice small portion off bottom of each tomato; scoop out pulp. Saute rest of ingredients until done.
Stuff into tomatoes. Place tops back on tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp noodle bake
directions: Combine cooked noodles, sour cream, soup, onions, olives, dill weed, seasoned salt and half of the cheese.
Fold in shrimp. Spoon into 2-quart dish (shallow dish).
