Cover with foil; fasten securely.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese and return to oven for about 15 minutes, until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: easy chicken roll-ups
directions: Bake chicken breasts, covered, until done.
Roll up cooked chicken breasts in crescent dough and bake as directed on can. Cook cream of chicken soup, using only half a can of milk and pour over crescent rolls and serve.
Makes 8 Chicken Roll-Ups.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water about 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
While noodles are cooking, in a large skillet, brown the ground beef, onions and green peppers.
Stir in tomato sauce and salt.
Remove from heat.
In a separate bowl, combine cottage cheese, sour cream and cream cheese.
In a 2-quart casserole, spread half the noodles, then cover with cheese mixture.
Add balance of noodles, top with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be prepared ahead of time.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine eggs and next 4 ingredients in a bowl; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until blended.
Add sweet potato mixture to dry ingredients; stir until moist.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix cornstarch, water and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
While hot, add strawberry Jell-O; stir until Jell-O mixture is dissolved.
Bake 2 pie shells and cool.
Place strawberries in pie shells and pour liquid over them.
Place in refrigerator for 3 hours before serving.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: hominy salad
directions: Drain hominy.
Dice pepper and onion.
Add remainder of ingredients and mix together.
Ready for serving.

title: brunch cheese dish
directions: Layer the sausage, bread and cheese in greased (9 x 12-inch) casserole, ending with cheese on top.
Mix eggs, milk and pepper; beat well and pour over top of other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until bubbly and slightly browned.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and pour over macaroni, cooked, drained and cooled.
Add chopped Cheddar, medium onion and bell pepper.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour.
Beat with mixer until very smooth.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blt dip
directions: Prepare bacon to crisp; set aside and let cool.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream.
Crumble cooked bacon into small pieces; add to mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put on toasted bread points.

title: carrot puree
directions: Boil carrots until soft.
Puree in Cuisinart all ingredients. Place in casserole and cool for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in half and half until smooth.
Cook (stirring constantly) until mixture thickens.
Stir in mustard, salt and pepper.
Arrange 1/2 of potatoes in 3-quart baking dish.
Cover with 1/2 of sauce.
Repeat with other 1/2 of potatoes and sauce.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: lemon dream cake
directions: Mix oil, water, eggs, grated lemon and cake mix, then add lemon Jell-O.
Mix for 5 minutes.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Empty bottle of barbecue sauce in pan.
Skim pieces of chicken and put in sauce.
Cook slowly for approximately 1 hour.
Let cool somewhat before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Use 1/2 pecans in ball and roll the ball in the rest of the pecans.
Roll ball in cheese.

title: sweet-n-sour beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain on paper toweling and crumble. Brown hamburger and chopped onion in bacon grease; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch dish or 3-quart Corning Ware.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: golden peach crunch
directions: Drain peaches and mix cornstarch.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon juice.
Turn into baking dish. Combine oats, butter and brown sugar until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: dessert cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into a ball and chill overnight.
(Roll ball in finely chopped pecans or crushed graham crackers.)
Serve with cinnamon graham crackers.

title: family meat loaf
directions: Crush cereal slightly.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well and stir in cereal.
Press into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve with chili sauce or catsup, if desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: danish apple squares
directions: Mix flour, salt and oleo like pie dough.
Add egg yolk.
Save egg white and add enough milk to make 3/4 cup milk.
Mix into dough.
Divide in half.
Roll out 9 x 15-inch pan and raise edges.

title: taco pie
directions: In 10-inch skillet, brown beef until crumbly.
Drain.
Add onion, green pepper, taco mix, tomato paste and water.
Mix well. Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add 1 1/2 cups of Monterey Jack cheese and all the Parmesan cheese to the meat mixture.
Set aside.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix thoroughly and bake for 1 1/2 hours in a 300° oven.

title: broiled tuna curry sandwiches
directions: Spread toast with margarine; arrange tomato slices on toast. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine tuna, mayonnaise, celery and curry powder.
Spoon onto tomato slices.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: shrimp-pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta following directions on package (directions may vary according to type of pasta).
Drain and set aside.
Thaw shrimp (if frozen); rinse and drain.
Drain and rinse olives and mushrooms. Add shrimp, olives and mushrooms to cooked pasta, then mix together.
Pour salad dressing over salad.
Mix again.
(More salad dressing may be added to taste, if desired.)
Chill for 6 hours or overnight.
Serve.

title: buddy's stuffed crabs
directions: Mommy buys pizza and cuts up and then we eat it.

title: supreme refried beans
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and fry until crispy.
Drain excess fat.
Put bacon back into pan with garlic and onion; fry for about 5 minutes.
Add pinto beans and mix with electric hand mixer, adding canned milk to desired consistency.
Add cheese. Warm beans until cheese is melted.
You may need to add more canned milk as the cheese melts.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Add cornstarch/water mixture to boiling ingredients.
Stir constantly and quickly until well blended and thickened; cook one minute longer.

title: crab appetizer
directions: Blend cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion and garlic salt by hand; spread on a shallow plate. Pour a bottle of chili sauce on the spread.
Layer crabmeat on top of the sauce.
Sprinkle the top with fresh parsley.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: nuteena a la king
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in margarine until tender.
Season to taste.
Add parsley and Nuteena and continue to brown at a low temperature.
Prepare white sauce and when mixture is slightly thickened, add grated cheese.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
If mixture becomes too thick, add more milk.
Combine the sliced eggs and Nuteena mixture with the white sauce and serve over the toasted bread.

title: "poke and pour cake"
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Bake cake.
Cool cake 15 minutes. Prepare jello as on package.
With fork, poke holes to bottom of cake.
Pour jello evenly over cake.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours. Before serving, cover with whipped cream.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Put 2 cups crushed corn flakes with 1/4 cup melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: town house squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes until set and lightly browned.

title: butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter and egg in mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Stir in flour and baking powder and blend well.
Cover and refrigerate for about 1 hour. Make 1-inch balls and bake at 375° until golden.

title: mexican dinner
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tomato, lettuce and cheese. Mix thoroughly.
Spoon into Crazy Crust.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes, until crust is deep golden brown.
Sprinkle with lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with taco sauce, if desired.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into large greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Fold in pineapple.
Put mixture into a greased dish.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers and melted butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together well.
Add others.
Pour into flat dish (8 x 8-inch) and freeze.
Garnish with strawberries and cut into squares.
Remove from freezer 1/2 hour before serving.

title: hamburger broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain. Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cook hamburger (add salt, pepper and onion flakes to taste); drain. Set aside.
Melt and mix the cream cheese and soup mix in hamburger; pour over the broccoli. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Lay crescent rolls flat on top.
Place in oven and brown at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble baked cake in large pieces.
Layer:
1/2 cake, 1/2 vanilla pudding, 1/2 pineapple, 1 banana, all blueberry filling. Repeat layers beginning with 1/2 cake, remainder of pudding and pineapple, 1 banana and all cherry pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: make ahead cabbage salad
directions: In large bowl, combine cabbage, tomatoes, green pepper, green onion, Cheddar cheese and carrots; mix well.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, milk and salt; whisk until smooth.
Pour over vegetables; toss gently.
Chill overnight.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: parboiling ribs before barbecuing
directions: Bring all ingredients but ribs to a boil.
Reduce to a simmer. Add ribs and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
Turn off heat and let sit 10 minutes more.

title: company beans
directions: Cook each package of vegetables separately and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients for sauce.
Keep at room temperature.
Place cooked vegetables in serving dish.
Top with sauce.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: In a saucepan, mix the cherries, water, sugar and vanilla. Bring to a boil.

title: hot tomato relish
directions: Mix and simmer for 2 hours.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni until done.
Do not overcook.
Mix macaroni and tuna, drained, into a large bowl.
Add vegetables and mix. Squeeze 10 drops of lemon juice, add Miracle Whip, relish and sugar.
Add more Miracle Whip to taste.

title: caramels
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt in a heavy pan.
Heat to boiling and cook to firm ball stage (242°).
In another pan, heat the butter and cream slightly.
Then add to sugar and syrup, stirring to keep from scorching.
Continue cooking and stirring constantly until mixture returns to firm ball stage.
Remove from heat; add flavoring and mix well.
Pour into 9-inch buttered pan. Cool.
(I cool overnight.)
Remove from pan; cut into squares.
Wrap in wax paper squares that you have already cut in 3-inch squares.

title: cheese filled jumbo shells
directions: Bring 5 to 6 quarts of water to a rapid boil.
Add the shells; boil for 10 minutes, avoiding over cooking.
Drain.
Cool in single layers on wax paper or aluminum foil to keep shells from sticking together.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer bread, cheese, ham, onion and broccoli in pan.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and mustard; blend well.
Pour egg mixture evenly over ham mixture.
Cover; refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 325°. Uncover; bake for 55 to 70 minutes or until done in center.
Makes 12 servings.

title: gold fingers
directions: Toast bread lightly.
Cover bread with cheese.
Place on foil covered cookie sheet.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes at 400° or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Remove from oven and cool.
Slice each piece into 4 strips (fingers) for a snack.

title: pineapple cherry upside down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In 13 x 9 baking pan melt butter.
Add pineapples and cherry pie filling to baking pan and mix in the creamed cheese.
Mix up the cake mix as instructed on box pour over mixture in pan and cover with nuts.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: chino valley pinto beans
directions: Wash beans and put in a 6-quart kettle.
Add water.
Bring to a simmer.
Cover and cook until tender, about 4 hours.
Mix remaining ingredients with the beans and the water.
Place in a 4-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 2 to 3 hours at 350° until done.

title: honey nut cheerios
directions: Pour some Cheerios in a bowl.
Pour a little milk on them. Then eat.

title: sour beef
directions: Pour the ingredients over the meat; let come to boil, then cook slowly until meat is tender but not overdone.
Use heavy pot. Add 1 cup sugar slowly (taste as you add sugar).
Soak gingersnaps, a little at a time, so they melt using water.
You will use almost a box of gingersnaps.
Add to the meat.
Make as thick as you like, then simmer about an hour, stirring once in a while.
Take out spices.
Serve over potato dumplings.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Butter decrusted bread.
Place bread slices in 10 x 15-inch pan. Mix eggs and milk.
Season and pour over bread.
Sprinkle browned and drained sausage over cheese.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake uncovered for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oysters wrapped in bacon
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Drain oysters and dry on paper towel. Cut bacon slices in half and lay an oyster on each piece. Cut a piece of cheese to fit on top, and fasten bacon around both with a toothpick.
Place oysters close together in a shallow baking dish, and cook about 10 minutes until bacon is crisp.
Can be served as hor d'oeuvres, or at a luncheon or dinner.

title: spanish chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken in water with carrot and onions.
Cool; chop or dice all of chicken.
Layer chicken, layer of Fritos and layer of cheese and repeat.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: marinade for round steak
directions: Mix together all ingredients except steak; marinate meat for 30 to 45 minutes, no longer!
Best broiled or barbecued.

title: no bake peanut butter drops
directions: Melt peanut butter, marshmallows, and butter over low heat (may use double boiler).
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Top with peanut butter immediately.
Remove from sheets when set.
Store at room temperature.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
This should be fluffy.
Chill until set, about 4 hours.
Garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with an electric mixer until well blended.
Melt chocolate in microwave, being careful not to scorch.
Mix into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into crusts.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool and refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight. Bake with a pan of water under cheesecake to prevent cracking.

title: million dollar torte
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 2 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Mix pudding, milk and cream cheese.
Spread over cake when cool.
Drain 32 ounce can crushed pineapple and put on top of pudding.
Top with Dream Whip or Cool Whip and chopped nuts. Refrigerate.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Place bacon drippings in Dutch oven. Shred cabbage.
Cut onions and green pepper very fine.
Place Dutch oven with bacon drippings.
Add salt and pepper (season to taste).
Cook until tender.
Add about one teaspoon and a half of brown sugar.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2 bread pans with Pam.
Combine the ingredients.
Pour into prepared pans and bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Leave bread in pan for 5 minutes to cool before removing from bread pans.

title: grilled chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients; mix well. Pour 1 cup marinade into a large resealable plastic bag. Add the chicken. Seal bag and turn to coat thoroughly. Refrigerate for at least 4 hours. Cover and refrigerate the remaining marinade for basting. Coat grill rack with nonstick cooking spray before starting the grill. Drain and discard marinade from chicken. Grill bone side down, covered, over indirect medium heat for 20 minutes. Turn; grill 20 to 30 minutes longer or until juices run clear, basting occasionally with reserved marinade.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger in a large skillet with onion until meat is no longer pink; drain. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix the ground beef, lettuce, onion, cheese, Doritos and tomato wedges.
Toss with Catalina dressing.

title: nut glazed brie
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together brown sugar, nuts and whiskey or brandy.
Cover and chill up to one week.
After one week, place cheese in a 9-inch pie plate or platter.
Bake in a 500° oven for 4 to 5 minutes or until cheese is slightly softened. Sprinkle sugar mixture over top.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes more or until sugar is melted and cheese is heated.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until done, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Put syrup and sugar in large container.
Use low heat to melt sugar.
Take off stove and melt in crunchy peanut butter.
Quickly stir in cornflakes.
Drop on wax paper or foil.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients in blender.
Add ice cubes a few at a time until thick.
For less fat, use 1% or skim milk.

title: edwardo's spinach souffle pizza
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes to proof.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add oil and water-yeast mixture. Knead until smooth, about 4 minutes.
Let rise in a warm place, about 1 hour.

Roll out slightly more than 1/2 of the dough into a round, about 1/4 inch thick, stretching by hand to cover pan area. Grease a 12-inch deep dish pan; sprinkle lightly with corn meal. Place dough into pan, allowing edges to overlap sides.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Blend margarine and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Then add vanilla and blend well.
Add flour into which soda has been added, alternately with sour cream.
Beat well.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325°.

title: frozen hash browns au'gratin
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 to 1-1/2 hours covered.
Uncover in the last few minutes and broil to brown the top.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Sift
together
the
flour,
salt
and
soda.
Combine butter,
sugar
and
water
over
low heat.
Bring to boil and remove
from
heat.
Add
vanilla and half of chocolate chips. Stir until chips are melted.
Pour mixture into a large mixing bowl;
beat
in eggs one at a time.
Blend in dry ingredients. Stir in remaining chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread into a 9 x 9-inch pan, well greased.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple cake icing
directions: Cook all ingredients over low heat, stirring constantly to a full boil, 2 to 3 minutes.
Cool and beat until spreading consistency.

title: praline and cream frozen dessert
directions: By hand, mix together the oatmeal, margarine, brown sugar, flour and pecans.
Bake in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Mixture should be crumbly.
Cool.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs. Beat well.
Add milk and cracker crumbs a little at a time.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and pineapple juice.
Makes 3 layers.
Grease cake pans and flour bottom and sides well.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar in bowl.
Add flour and nuts. Mix.
Make a crumb mix.
Save 1 cup for top.
Press mix into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350° until light brown.
Blend sugar with cheese, eggs, milk, lemon and vanilla in mixer.
Beat well.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle top with crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
When cool, cut into 2-inch squares.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Chop onions and chip beef up.
Mix all ingredients together. Shape and roll in parsley flakes.
Pack in container.
It will mold to container used; place Saran Wrap in container first for easier removal.

title: stuffed meatballs
directions: Make your hamburger into patties. Cook your dressing according to directions.
Take in ice cream dipper and put 1 scoop of dressing on each hamburger patty.
Take and pull the hamburger up around the dressing until it is completely covered.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Bring out of oven and pour the soup over each meatball and place back in the oven for 5 to 7 minutes more.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Mix all together; bake in greased casserole dish at 400 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon bread pudding
directions: In large mixing bowl, whisk eggs; blend in milk, half and half, sugar and vanilla until combined. Stir in bread cubes until lightly moistened. Grease a 2-quart rectangular baking dish and spread mixture in evenly. Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes or until center starts to firm.

title: chocolate "bread"
directions: Butter and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 300°. Melt chocolate in water with coffee over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in chocolate mixture.

title: white trash
directions: Pour sugar in paper bag.
Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add Chex.
Pour into bag.
Shake until coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: saxapash
directions: Brown beef.
Add salt, sugar, garlic salt and tomato sauce. Simmer 20 minutes. Chop onions and mix with sour cream and cream cheese that are room temperature.
Cook noodles as directed.
In buttered casserole, place a layer of noodles, layer of cream cheese mixture and a layer of meat mixture.
Repeat.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 6.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Combine flour, milk and mayonnaise into bowl.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet or into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hungarian beef goulash
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven until hot.
Cook and stir beef until brown (15 minutes).
Drain.
Add water, tomatoes with liquid, onions, garlic, paprika, salt, bouillon, broth, caraway seed and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add green pepper.
Cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve in soup bowls with French bread.

title: easy creamy chocolate frosting
directions: In medium microwave-safe bowl, place butter and shortening. Microwave on High for 1 minute or until butter is melted.
Add cocoa and salt; stir until smooth.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add powdered sugar alternately with milk, beating on medium speed of electric mixer until smooth and of desired consistency.
Add additional milk if needed.
Stir in vanilla.
Makes about 2 cups frosting.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Fry and drain hamburger.
Mix with taco sauce.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish as bottom layer.
Layer on green beans, cheese and Durkee onions. Add blended and prepared corn muffin mix as top. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: In a saucepan, cook the Brussels sprouts, cauliflower, broccoli and carrots in a small amount of liquid, salted boiling water, until tender-crisp; drain.

title: succotash
directions: Place in a large pot all ingredients, except corn.
Bring to boil; cover pot.
Lower heat and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add more water, if needed.
Water should cover beans throughout cooking time.
Serve with hot corn bread and fried chicken.

title: chili-o chicken
directions: Lightly grease skillet.
Arrange chicken in single layer. Cover and cook slow for 30 minutes.
Pour can of tomatoes, seasoning mix and water.
Continue to cook 15 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.
A bit spicy, but yummy.

title: persimmon nut bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, persimmon pulp and vanilla.
Mix.
Beat well.
Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder (sifted together).
Mix until blended; add raisins and nuts.
Divide batter into two well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Remove from pans and cool on rack.

title: mexe taco pie
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning mix and 1 cup picante.
Simmer 5 to 8 minutes; remove from heat. Stir in egg.
Sprinkle frozen pie crust with 1/2 cup cheese; top with green chilies.
Pour ground beef mixture over chilies.
Top with remaining 1 cup cheese; sprinkle tortilla chips over top. Bake in preheated 350° oven on preheated baking sheet 20 to 25 minutes.
Garnish with shredded lettuce, sour cream and remaining picante.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fiesta ranch green chili dip
directions: Combine dip mix with sour cream.
Stir in chilies, olives and cheese.
Serve with chips, vegetables or crackers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: baked salmon croquettes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in well-greased muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: texas pie
directions: Crust: Mix flour, margarine, pecans and 1/2 cup powdered sugar. Mix well. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: quick turkey curry
directions: Cook the onion in butter. Add the soup and milk; heat and stir until smooth. Stir in the sour cream and curry powder. Add the turkey or chicken; heat. Garnish with snipped parsley and raisins. Serve over fluffy hot cooked rice. Serves 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Bring to boil the raisins and coffee.
Cook for 5 minutes; add Crisco, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and cook 10 minutes more.
Cool. Sift flour and soda together.
Add to coffee mixture a small amount at a time.
Mix well after each.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour in 2 loaf pans, greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: mom's e-z corned beef hash casserole
directions: Take Veg-All, drain and pour in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Add corned beef hash.
Spread out over top of veggies.
Place in 425° oven about 20 minutes or until corned beef has browned a little.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and chips. Pour into greased baking dish. Cover with grated cheese. Then top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 375° for 10 to 20 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: spicy marinated mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms with damp towel.
In a jar with a tight fitting lid, shake remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Pour over mushrooms; cover and marinate in refrigerator at least 12 hours. Stir or turn occasionally.
Serve as an appetizer or in a salad.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil.
Stir until all ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, nuts, pineapple and bananas.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Form into a ball and refrigerate.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350° in a buttered baking pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
except
can soup and water. Shape into balls; arrange in a pan.
Pour the remaining celery soup and water over meatballs.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: egg casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Drain liquid from peas and reserve.
Slice potatoes and eggs.
Layer potatoes, eggs and peas in casserole.
Repeat 3 times.
Simmer onion in 2 tablespoons butter in the top pan of a double boiler over direct heat.
Add flour and make roux.
Add drained pea juice and milk to make 2 cups of liquid.
Put top pan in double boiler over water until thickened.
Stir continuously.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over casserole.
Top with bread crumbs mixed with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: some-ore
directions: Brown beef; stir to keep separated and remove excess fat.
Add onion, green pepper and celery and saute.
Place in casserole. Add all other ingredients except noodles.
Mix slightly.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Place 1 cup Chinese noodles over top and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Add onion soup mix, mushroom soup, noodles and water.
Salt to taste.
Cook about 20 minutes until noodles are done.
Add sour cream.
Cook 3 more minutes.
